  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b94">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/AnalogueDial"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000345">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2826"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2824"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2825"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2823"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2822"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000084"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Scrubber(x) ↔ Separator(x) ∧ ∃f,p,g,l (SeparationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f) ∧ LiquidWashingProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p) ∧ GasPortion(g) ∧ LiquidPortion(l) ∧ hasInput(x,g) ∧ hasInput(x,l)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">scrubber</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">lavador de gases</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A reactor that removes various components from produced gas.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A distillation column intended to clean gas by washing the gas flow with water or with another liquid entering at the top of the vessel and sprayed in the gas. Typically to remove dust and small particles.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A distillation column intended to clean gas by washing the gas flow with water or with another liquid entering at the top of the vessel and sprayed in the gas. Typically to remove dust and small particles.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A device to remove dirt, water, foreign matter, or undesired liquids that are part of the gas flowstream.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SCRUBBER&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;SEPARATOR&gt; intended to clean gas by washing the gas flow with water or with another liquid entering at the top of the vessel and sprayed in the gas. Typically to remove dust and small particles</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A scrubber is a separator that cleans gas by washing the gas flow with liquid to remove contaminants such as dust, particles, or undesired substances.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um lavador de gases é um separador que limpa gás através da lavagem do fluxo gasoso com líquido para remover contaminantes como poeira, partículas ou substâncias indesejadas.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every scrubber is a separator that has the function of separation and participates in liquid washing processes with both gas and liquid inputs.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000348">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um aríete de corte é um aríete que possui função de corte de tubulação e tem lâminas de corte endurecidas projetadas para cortar a coluna de perfuração ou tubulação durante operações de prevenção de blowout.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A shear ram is a ram that bears a pipe shearing function and has hardened cutting blades designed to cut drillpipe or tubing during blowout prevention operations.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">shear ram</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">aríete de corte</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SHEAR RAM&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;RAM&gt; that is a closure mechanism on a wells blowout-preventer stack fitted with chisel-like jaws that are hydraulically operated. When the ram is closed on the pipe, the jaws or blades cut the pipe, permitting the upper section to be removed from the BOP stack</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A ram in the BOP that shears off the pipe.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A blowout preventer (BOP) closing element fitted with hardened tool steel blades designed to cut the drillpipe or tubing when the BOP is closed, and then fully close to provide isolation or sealing of the wellbore.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A shear valve is a ram-type BOP, similar in operation to a gate valve, but uses a pair of opposing steel plungers, rams. The rams extend toward the centre of the wellbore to restrict flow or retract open in order to permit flow.</skos:definition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2894"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every shear ram is a ram that has the function to shear pipe and has shearing blades as component parts at all times.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(ShearRam(x) ↔ Ram(x) ∧ ∃f(PipeShearingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃b(ShearingBlade(b) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,b)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/DisplacementMechanism">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">displacement mechanism</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">mecanismo de deslocamento</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000333">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">power transformer secondary winding</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">enrolamento secundário de transformador de potência</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive classification basis - the physical configuration (being the secondary winding of a power transformer) provides necessary conditions, but sufficient conditions are harder to assert under OWA without risking false positives for specialized or hybrid transformer configurations.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/SecondaryWinding"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2559"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(PowerTransformerSecondaryWinding(x) → FiatObjectPart(x) ∧ ∃y(PowerTransformer(y) ∧ partOf(x,y)) ∧ ∃f(SecondaryWindingFunction(f) ∧ hasFunction(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">PowerTransformerSecondaryWinding SubClassOf FiatObjectPart and (partOf some PowerTransformer) and (hasFunction some SecondaryWindingFunction)</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma FiatObjectPart que é o enrolamento secundário de um transformador de potência e que possui uma SecondaryWindingFunction consistindo em fornecer energia elétrica transformada no nível de tensão de saída.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A FiatObjectPart that is the secondary winding of a power transformer and that bears a SecondaryWindingFunction consisting in delivering transformed electrical power at the output voltage level.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;POWER TRANSFORMER SECONDARY WINDING&gt; is a &lt;TRANSFORMER SECONDARY WINDING&gt; intended to be the secondary winding of a power transformer</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1368">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/SignalProcessingUnit"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1783">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/MultipleConnections"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/VesselInlet">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">vessel inlet</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">entrada de vaso</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000332">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um enrolamento de transformador que é parte de um transformador de potência e que serve como enrolamento primário recebendo energia elétrica de entrada para transformação eletromagnética.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A TransformerWinding that is part of a power transformer and that serves as the primary winding receiving input electrical power for electromagnetic transformation.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;POWER TRANSFORMER PRIMARY WINDING&gt; is a &lt;TRANSFORMER PRIMARY WINDING&gt; intended to be the winding of a power transformer</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">enrolamento de transformador</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">power transformer primary winding</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type based on structural position within power transformer. Under OWA, sufficient conditions for primary winding configuration would risk false positives for specialized or hybrid transformer components that contain primary-like windings but should not be classified as standard power transformer primary windings.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2554"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PrimaryWinding"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(PowerTransformerPrimaryWinding(x) → TransformerWinding(x) ∧ ∃y(PowerTransformer(y) ∧ partOf(x,y)) ∧ ∃f(PrimaryWindingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">PowerTransformerPrimaryWinding is-a TransformerWinding that is-part-of PowerTransformer and has-function PrimaryWindingFunction</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000087">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[isa5_1] a device, other than a common, hand-actuated process block valve or self-actuated check valve, that directly manipulates the flow of one or more fluid process streams.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A valve that can be used to modify (regulate) the fluid flow rate in a process control system. It usually includes an actuator, which responds to a signal from the controlling system and changes the position of the flow controlling element in the valve.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] Modulating valve that controls either the flow rate, liquid level, or pressure in process equipment. In the latter case, it is often referred to as a (pressure) regulator.                   (Note - Typically, high pressure gas from the pipeline is used as the supply medium needed to energize the valve actuator.) https://www.ipieca.org/resources/methane-emissions-glossary</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A valve that controls a process variable, such as pressure, flow or temperature, by modulating its opening in response to a signal from a controller.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CONTROL VALVE&gt; is a &lt;VALVE&gt; and an &lt;FINAL CONTROL FUNCTION&gt;, operated by an &lt;ACTUATOR&gt; that can be used to modify the fluid flow rate in response to a signal from a &lt;CONTROLLER&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A valve that can be used to modify (regulate)  the fluid flow rate in a process control system. It usually includes an actuator, which responds to a signal from the controlling system and changes the position of the flow controlling element in the valve.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000077"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b658"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b657"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A control valve is a valve that is equipped with an actuator and regulates fluid flow rate in response to control signals from a process control system.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula de controle é uma válvula que é equipada com um atuador e regula a vazão de fluido em resposta a sinais de controle de um sistema de controle de processo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">control valve</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula de controle</rdfs:label>
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000087"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">ControlValve(x) → Valve(x) ∧ ∃a(Actuator(a) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,a)) ∧ ∃f(FlowControlFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∀p(participatesIn(x,p) ∧ FlowControlProcess(p) → ∃s(ControlSignal(s) ∧ hasInput(p,s)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every control valve is a valve that has an actuator as component part and has a flow control function and participates in flow control processes by receiving control signals and modulating fluid flow.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Control valve is a functional type where identity is grounded in the designed function to regulate flow in response to control signals. This functional identity cannot be reduced to structural checklists as the same function can be realized through many different physical mechanisms (ball, butterfly, globe, gate, etc.). The presence of actuator and flow control element are necessary but not sufficient - the key is the integration for automated flow modulation.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/TubingSupportFunction">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3209"/>
