  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000214">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">basin</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">bacia</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma bacia é um vaso projetado para armazenar material líquido ou sólido, caracterizado por ser tipicamente aberto no topo e instalado parcial ou totalmente abaixo do nível do solo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A basin is a vessel that is designed to store liquid or solid material, characterized by being typically open at the top and installed partly or totally below grade.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">Basin(x) ↔ Vessel(x) ∧ ∃f(StorageFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃p(OpenTop(p) ∧ hasGeometricProperty(x,p)) ∧ ∃q(PartlyBelowGrade(q) ∧ hasInstallationProperty(x,q))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000214"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A large area with a general containment and an often thick accumulation of rock. A sedimentary basin is an area of regional settling that can be characterized in space, time, and sedimentary fill .It is a physical depression at the earth's surface which accumulates and preserves sediments. The scale of basins varies greatly, from ocean basins to small ponds.                  ==References==                   Helwig, J. A. 1985. Origin and Classification of Sedimentary Basins. Offshore Technology Conference. http://www.doi.org/doi:10.4043/4843-MS</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A depression in the crust of the Earth, caused by plate tectonic activity and subsidence, in which sediments accumulate.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A container intended to store liquid or solid material partly or totally below grade and that is typically open.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;BASIN&gt; is a &lt;FLUID CONTAINER&gt;, intended to store liquid or solid material partly or totally below grade and that is typically open</skos:definition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b187"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every basin is a vessel that bears a storage function and has an open top configuration and is installed partly below grade.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1320">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000068"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/EnclosedSpace">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">enclosed space</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">espaço fechado</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000320">
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2351"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A facility on a pipeline for inserting and retrieving a scraper or pig.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;PIG TRAP&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;TOOL&gt; that is a pipeline maintenance tool, which includes a launcher and receiver, introducing a &lt;PIPE PIG&gt; into the line</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] "</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma armadilha de pig é um conjunto que possui a função de lançar e receber pigs de tubulação para manutenção de dutos e possui componentes de lançador e receptor.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A pig trap is an assembly that bears the function of launching and receiving pipe pigs for pipeline maintenance and has both launcher and receiver components.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(PigTrap(x) ↔ Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(PigLaunchingAndReceivingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃l(PigLauncher(l) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,l)) ∧ ∃r(PigReceiver(r) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,r)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pig trap</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">armadilha de pig</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every pig trap is an assembly that bears a pig launching and receiving function and has component parts that are a pig launcher and a pig receiver.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3090">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000173"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1721">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000192"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000228">
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000228"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">christmas tree</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">árvore de natal</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CHRISTMAS TREE&gt; is a &lt;PIPING SYSTEM&gt; that is an assembly of pipes and piping parts, with valves and associated control equipment that is connected to the top of a wellhead and is intended for control of fluid from a well.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] The control sections that sits above the basic wellhead. It may contain hangers, master valves, annular valves, wing valves, and gauges or pressure, flow rate or monitoring measurement equipment.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] The set of valves, spools, and fittings connected to the top of a well to direct and control the flow of formation fluids from the well.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] An 'artefact' that is an assembly of pipes and piping parts, with valves and associated control equipment that is connected to the top of a wellhead and is intended for control of fluid from a well.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that is an assembly of pipes and piping parts, with valves and associated control equipment that is connected to the top of a wellhead and is intended for control of fluid from a well.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every christmas tree is an assembly that has the function to control well fluids and is connected to a wellhead and has master valves as component parts.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma árvore de natal é um conjunto que possui uma função de controle de fluidos de poço, está conectada a uma cabeça de poço, e contém válvulas mestras para controlar fluidos de formação de poços de petróleo e gás.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A christmas tree is an assembly that bears a well fluid control function, is connected to a wellhead, and contains master valves for controlling formation fluids from oil and gas wells.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (ChristmasTree(x) ↔ (Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(WellFluidControlFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃w(Wellhead(w) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,w)) ∧ ∃v(MasterValve(v) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,v))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b498"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/CuttingsAndFluid">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">fluido de cascalhos de e</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">cuttings and fluid</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
