  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000244">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DEMISTER&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that is capable of &lt;DEMISTING&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object intended to catch fluid droplets.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Demister(x) ↔ Separator(x) ∧ ∃f(DemistingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">demister</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">demister</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every demister is a separator that has the function of demisting gas streams by coalescing and removing entrained liquid droplets.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b848"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um demister é um separador que possui uma função de desmistificação para remover gotículas de líquido de correntes gasosas através de mecanismos de coalescência.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A demister is a separator that bears a demisting function for removing liquid droplets from gas streams through coalescence mechanisms.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000297">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] The outside steel case of a cartridge or a sonde in a wireline logging tool.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;HOUSING&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and an &lt;ENCLOSURE&gt; and a &lt;SUPPORT&gt; that, next to separation, also provides support</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] An enclosure that also provides support.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um Assembly que possui tanto uma EnclosureFunction quanto uma SupportFunction, fornecendo limites protetivos ao redor de componentes internos enquanto os suporta estruturalmente.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An Assembly that bears both an EnclosureFunction and a SupportFunction, providing protective boundaries around internal components while structurally supporting them.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type based on physical configuration. Under OWA, sufficient conditions would force any assembly with enclosure and support functions to be classified as a standard housing, potentially misclassifying specialized equipment with housing-like properties but different maintenance categories.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Housing SubClassOf Assembly and (bearerOf some EnclosureFunction) and (bearerOf some SupportFunction)</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Housing(x) → Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f₁(EnclosureFunction(f₁) ∧ bearerOf(x,f₁)) ∧ ∃f₂(SupportFunction(f₂) ∧ bearerOf(x,f₂)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1842"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">carcaça</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">housing</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000249">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions because this is a constructive type defined by physical mechanism. Under OWA, any pump with a flexible diaphragm component could be classified as a diaphragm pump, but there may be hybrid or specialized equipment containing diaphragms that should not be automatically classified into this maintenance category.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A reciprocating pump intended to pump a liquid with a small capacity. This is done by means of thin flexible diaphragms to seal pumped fluid from leakage to atmosphere.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DIAPHRAGM PUMP&gt; is a &lt;RECIPROCATING PUMP&gt; intended to pump a liquid with a small capacity. This is done by means of thin flexible diaphragms to seal pumped fluid from leakage to atmosphere; flow rate is achieved through reciprocatory motion of the diaphragm</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">diaphragm pump</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">bomba de diafragma</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma bomba de diafragma é uma bomba alternativa que usa diafragmas flexíveis para deslocar líquido e selar o fluido bombeado contra vazamento atmosférico.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A diaphragm pump is a reciprocating pump that uses flexible diaphragms to displace liquid and seal the pumped fluid from atmospheric leakage.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(DiaphragmPump(x) → (ReciprocatingPump(x) ∧ ∃d(FlexibleDiaphragm(d) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,d)) ∧ ∃p(DiaphragmSealing(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every diaphragm pump is a reciprocating pump that has flexible diaphragm as component part at all times and participates in diaphragm sealing.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000337"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b932"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b931"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b930"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000109">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">manômetro de pressão diferencial</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">differential pressure gauge</rdfs:label>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b979"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A gauge that is intended for measuring and indicating pressure differences.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DIFFERENTIAL PRESSURE GAUGE&gt; is a &lt;PRESSURE GAUGE&gt; and a &lt;DIFFERENTIAL PRESSURE MEASURING INSTRUMENT&gt; using a &lt;DIFFERENTIAL PRESSURE MEASURING ELEMENT&gt;</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every differential pressure gauge is a pressure gauge that bears a DifferentialPressureMeasurementFunction and has component parts including a DifferentialPressureMeasuringElement and PressurePortPair.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A differential pressure gauge is a pressure gauge that measures and indicates the difference between two pressure inputs using a differential pressure measuring element.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um manômetro de pressão diferencial é um manômetro que mede e indica a diferença entre duas entradas de pressão usando um elemento de medição de pressão diferencial.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (DifferentialPressureGauge(x) ↔ PressureGauge(x) ∧ ∃f(DifferentialPressureMeasurementFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃e(DifferentialPressureMeasuringElement(e) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,e)) ∧ ∃p(PressurePortPair(p) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/DistillationProcess">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">distillation process</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de destilação</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2397">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/CurvedFluidPassage"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/EnclosureFunction">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b393"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3205"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1839"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b608"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b421"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b394"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1697"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2661"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b420"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b464"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b463"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2660"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3204"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b609"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1751"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/DesignedFunction"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1698"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1752"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1838"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in an EnclosureProcess and that consists in providing a structural boundary that houses and protects internal mechanical components from the environment while maintaining structural integrity.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in an EnclosureProcess and that consists in providing a protective boundary that separates an internal space from the external environment while providing structural support for contained components.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in an EnclosureProcess and that consists in providing a structural boundary that contains and directs fluid flow while accommodating internal flow control components.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in an EnclosureProcess and that consists in providing physical containment and environmental protection for internal components or systems.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in an EnclosureProcess and that consists in providing a protective housing or containment boundary for internal components or mechanisms.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in an EnclosureProcess and that consists in providing a protective boundary that contains, supports, and isolates internal components from external environment while maintaining structural integrity.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in an EnclosureProcess and that consists in providing a protective boundary around internal components while maintaining structural integrity and enabling controlled fluid flow through integral connection points.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in an EnclosureProcess and that consists in providing protective containment and structural support for internal mechanical components, maintaining their spatial arrangement and protecting them from external environmental conditions.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">enclosure function</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de proteção e invólucro</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2690">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/RelayCoil"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b302">
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/BottomHoleDrillingProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000304">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An injection pump is a pump that is specifically designed to inject fluid into reservoirs or production systems, typically at relatively high pressures.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma bomba de injeção é uma bomba especificamente projetada para injetar fluido em reservatórios ou sistemas de produção, tipicamente em pressões relativamente altas.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every injection pump is a pump that bears an injection function for delivering fluids to reservoirs or production systems.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">bomba de injeção</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">injection pump</rdfs:label>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1980"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;INJECTION PUMP&gt; is a &lt; POSITIVE DISPLACEMENT PUMP&gt; that is typically applied for relatively high pressures in case of injection systems</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] Any pump used to inject fluid into the reservoir or production system.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(InjectionPump(x) ↔ Pump(x) ∧ ∃f(InjectionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000310">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">célula de carga</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">load cell</rdfs:label>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2152"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every load cell is an instrument that bears a force-to-electrical transduction function and has a force-receiving element, transduction element, and electrical output.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;LOAD CELL&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;FORCE MEASURING ELEMENT&gt; and a &lt;TRANSDUCER&gt; that converts a force such as tension, compression, pressure, or torque into an electrical signal that can be measured</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A device based on strain gauge technology that helps measure the surface weight of coiled tubing.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] The sensor component in a weight-indicator system that detects the tensional or compressional forces being imparted to the running string at surface.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A transducer which produces a signal with a defined relationship to the force applied to it.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A load cell is an instrument that converts mechanical force (tension, compression, pressure, or torque) into a proportional electrical signal for measurement purposes.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma célula de carga é um instrumento que converte força mecânica (tração, compressão, pressão ou torque) em um sinal elétrico proporcional para fins de medição.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (LoadCell(x) ↔ Instrument(x) ∧ ∃f(ForceToElectricalTransductionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1811">
    <owl:intersectionOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1813"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000136">
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(OrificePlate(x) → FlowMeasuringElement(x) ∧ ∃p,h(ThinPlate(p) ∧ SpecifiedHole(h) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,p) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,h)) ∧ ∃f(FlowMeasurementFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2280"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2279"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000082"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">orifice plate</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">placa de orifício</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive classification based on physical structure. Under OWA, any plate with a hole could potentially be classified as an orifice plate, but many perforated plates serve different purposes (structural, filtering, etc.). The structural differentia alone is not sufficient without industrial context validation.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma placa de orifício é um elemento de medição de fluxo que consiste de uma placa fina com um orifício especificado através do qual o fluido flui para criar pressão diferencial para medição da taxa de fluxo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An orifice plate is a flow measuring element that consists of a thin plate with a specified hole through which fluid flows to create differential pressure for flow rate measurement.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] Part of an orifice metering system. A plate with a hole through which a single phase flow produces a pressure drop.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that is a thin plate with a specified hole in the middle. It is usually placed in a pipe to measure the rate of fluid flow.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every orifice plate is a flow measuring element that has a thin plate component and has a specified hole component and bears a flow measurement function.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ElectricalCurrent">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">electrical current</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">corrente elétrico</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3048">
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ElectricalCircuitControlProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FiltrationProcess">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">filtration process</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de filtração</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which particles, contaminants, or unwanted substances are selectively retained from a fluid stream by a filter element through mechanical screening or other separation mechanisms while clean fluid passes through.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2102">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/LevelSwitchingFunction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/BearingSystem">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">sistema de mancal</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">bearing system</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1183">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000342"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b728">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FlowMeasurementProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1098">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PowerTransmissionProcess"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000295">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] The device used to facilitate the addition of drilling fluid additives to the whole mud system.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;HOPPER&gt; is a &lt;CONTAINER&gt; with a conical shape that is intended to store solids for filling or dosing purposes</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] Mixing chamber where dry components can be evenly mixed with liquids. The dry materials are introduced at the bottom of the hopper through a nozzle.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A vessel with a conical shape for filling or dosing purposes</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A vessel with a conical shape for filling or dosing purposes.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">hopper</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">hopper</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A hopper is a vessel that is designed to store solid materials and dispense them through a controlled discharge opening.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um hopper é um vaso projetado para armazenar materiais sólidos e dispensá-los através de uma abertura de descarga controlada.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1822"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every hopper is a vessel that bears a SolidStorageAndDispensingFunction and has a SolidDischargeOpening as component part.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Hopper(x) ↔ (Vessel(x) ∧ ∃f(SolidStorageAndDispensingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃p(SolidDischargeOpening(p) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,p))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1166">
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1161"/>
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1167"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000353">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um atuador solenoide é um atuador elétrico que utiliza um solenoide linear de serviço contínuo para converter energia elétrica em energia mecânica através de um êmbolo com curso axial em ação de empurrar ou puxar.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A solenoid actuator is an electric actuator that utilizes a continuous duty linear solenoid to convert electrical energy into mechanical power via a plunger with an axial stroke in either a push or pull action.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(SolenoidActuator(x) → ElectricActuator(x) ∧ ∃s(Solenoid(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)) ∧ ∃p(Plunger(p) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">atuador solenoide</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">solenoid actuator</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000207"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000260"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2972"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type defined by solenoid mechanism. Under OWA, sufficient conditions would force any device with solenoid and plunger components to be classified as a solenoid actuator, potentially misclassifying complex hybrid devices or specialized equipment containing solenoid components but serving different primary functions.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every solenoid actuator is an electric actuator that has a solenoid as component part and has a plunger as component part and converts electrical power to linear mechanical motion.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SOLENOID ACTUATOR&gt; is an &lt;ELECTRIC ACTUATOR&gt; and an &lt;ELECTRIC TO MECHANICAL ENERGY CONVERTER&gt; and an &lt;ELECTROMECHANICAL DEVICE&gt;  that is utilizing a continuous duty linear solenoid to convert electrical energy into mechanical power via a plunger with an axial stroke in either a push or pull action</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b614">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/CondensationProcess"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000302">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] In electromagnetics or electrical circuit theory, the ratio of voltage to current when these are represented by phasor quantities in alternating current circuits. (A phasor is a complex number that represents the amplitude and phase of a quantity that varies sinusoidally in time.) Electrical impedance, also symbolized by Z, is a complex number that has the same units (ohms) as resistivity.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[DEXPI] An energy converter component that is an assembly of rotating vanes within an enclosure which is used to impart energy to or derive energy from a fluid through dynamic force (from ``_).</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] The rotating pump component that drives the fluid in a centrifugal pump.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;IMPELLER&gt; is a &lt;MECHANICAL TO MECHANICAL ENERGY CONVERTER&gt; that is an assembly of rotating vanes within an enclosure which is used to impart energy to or derive energy from a fluid through dynamic force</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">impeller</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">impulsor</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um impulsor é um conjunto que consiste em pás rotativas montadas em um cubo que transfere energia para ou de fluidos através de força rotacional dinâmica dentro de um invólucro.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An impeller is an assembly consisting of rotating vanes mounted on a hub that transfers energy to or from fluids through dynamic rotational force within an enclosure.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive classification based on physical mechanism. Under OWA, defining sufficient conditions for the rotating vane assembly could lead to false positives where other rotating equipment with vanes (like turbine rotors or fan assemblies) might be incorrectly classified as impellers when they should remain in their specific equipment categories.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Impeller(x) → Assembly(x) ∧ ∃v,h(RotatingVanes(v) ∧ Hub(h) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,v) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,h) ∧ ∃m(RotationalMotion(m) ∧ participatesIn(x,m)) ∧ ∃f(EnergyTransferFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1928"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1926"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1927"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every impeller is an assembly that has rotating vanes and a hub as component parts at all times, participates in rotational motion, and bears an energy transfer function.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2643">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PumpingProcess"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000230">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">compensator</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">compensador</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um compensador é um artefato material que tem a função projetada de compensar movimento axial ou radial entre dois elementos conectados.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A compensator is a material artifact that has the designed function of compensating for axial or radial movement between two connected elements.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;COMPENSATOR&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that has a capability of &lt;COMPENSATING&gt; for axial or radial movement between two elements that is connected</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A device compensating for axial or radial movement between two elements that is connected.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Compensator(x) ↔ MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃f(MovementCompensationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b584"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every compensator is a material artifact that bears a movement compensation function and has component parts including a compensation mechanism and connection interfaces.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/TransductionFunction">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3161"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3162"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/DesignedFunction"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de transdução</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">transduction function</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2425">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FluidTransportProcess"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1133">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/SuctionInlet"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2275">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FlowMeasurementProcess"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000361">
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3146"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;THREE-PHASE SEPARATOR&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;FLUID SEPARATOR&gt; intended to separate three fluids in different phases, typically gas and liquid and water</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A separator intended to separate three fluids in different phases, typically gas and liquid and water</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A vessel that separates the well fluids into gas and two types of liquids: oil and water.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every three-phase separator is a separator that has the function of separating fluid into gas, oil, and water phases, and has gas outlet, oil outlet, and water outlet as component parts.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um separador trifásico é um separador que possui uma função de separação trifásica para separar fluidos de poço em fases gasosa, oleosa e aquosa.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A three-phase separator is a separator that bears a three-phase separation function to separate well fluids into gas, oil, and water phases.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (ThreePhaseSeparator(x) ↔ (Separator(x) ∧ ∃f (ThreePhaseSeparationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">three phase separator</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">separador trifásico</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000186">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1013"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000031"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1014"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de transmissão de pressão diferencial</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">differential pressure transmission function</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b755">
    <rdf:rest rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#nil"/>
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b753"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000264">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] An internal combustion engine that is an induction compression ignition exhaust engine which ignites a fuel air mixture.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;ENGINE&gt; is a &lt;MOTOR&gt; and a &lt;MACHINE&gt; that converts energy into mechanical force and motion</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um motor é um motor que converte energia de combustível químico em força mecânica e movimento através de processos de combustão.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An engine is a motor that converts chemical fuel energy into mechanical force and motion through combustion processes.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1226"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1225"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1228"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1227"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000315"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">engine</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">motor</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every Engine is a Motor that has function MechanicalEnergyGenerationFunction and has input ChemicalFuelPortion and participates in CombustionProcess.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Engine(x) ↔ Motor(x) ∧ ∃f(MechanicalEnergyGenerationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃p(ChemicalFuelPortion(p) ∧ hasInput(x,p)) ∧ ∃c(CombustionProcess(c) ∧ participatesIn(x,c)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3285">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/UninterruptedPowerSupplyProcess"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1640">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/TurbomachineryPowerGenerationProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000277">
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1471"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1470"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000339"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1469"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(FlexibleRiser(x) → Riser(x) ∧ ∃q(FlexibleProperty(q) ∧ hasQuality(x,q)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">riser flexível</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flexible riser</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FLEXIBLE RISER&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;RISER&gt; that is a flexible vertical or near vertical pipe for the flow of liquid or gas between the seabed and the surface</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A flexible vertical or near vertical pipe for the flow of liquid or gas between the seabed and the surface.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um riser flexível é um riser que possui construção de material flexível permitindo condução de fluido vertical ou quase vertical entre o fundo do mar e a superfície, acomodando o movimento da embarcação.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A flexible riser is a riser that has flexible material construction allowing vertical or near-vertical fluid conduction between seabed and surface while accommodating vessel movement.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every flexible riser is a riser that has a flexible property</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type where flexibility is a material/structural property. Under OWA, asserting equivalence would force any pipe with flexible qualities to be classified as a flexible riser, even if it serves different functions or has different deployment contexts. Starting with necessary conditions protects against false positives.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3422">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/WellSurfaceControlProcess"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000092">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um trocador de calor é um vaso de pressão que possui a função projetada de transferir energia térmica entre duas ou mais correntes de fluido mantendo sua separação.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A heat exchanger is a pressure vessel that bears the designed function of transferring thermal energy between two or more fluid streams while maintaining their separation.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">heat exchanger</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">trocador de calor</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that is intended to transfer heat from one object to another.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;HEAT EXCHANGER&gt; is an &lt;EXCHANGER&gt; that has the capability of &lt;HEAT EXCHANGING&gt;</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1792"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (HeatExchanger(x) ↔ (Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(HeatTransferFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every heat exchanger is an assembly that has the function of heat transfer and has component parts including heat transfer surfaces and fluid passages for separated streams.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PressureSignalTransmissionProcess">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de transmissão de sinal de pressão</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pressure signal transmission process</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000035"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000231">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000222"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b612"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">compressor casing</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">Invólucro</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type based on structural configuration. Under OWA, sufficient conditions for compressor-specific casing identity could lead to false positives where any enclosure intended for compressors might be classified as a standard compressor casing, including specialized or hybrid enclosures that warrant distinct classification.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (CompressorCasing(x) → (Casing(x) ∧ ∃y (Compressor(y) ∧ intendedForUseWith(x,y))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">CompressorCasing ⊑ Casing ⊓ ∃intendedForUseWith.Compressor</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A Casing that is intended for housing compressor internals including the shaft with impellers and other compressor-specific mechanical components.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um Invólucro que é destinado a abrigar componentes internos do compressor, incluindo o eixo com impulsores e outros componentes mecânicos específicos do compressor.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;COMPRESSOR CASING&gt; is a  &lt;CASING&gt; that is the typical enclosure for compressors housing the shaft with impeller(s) and other compressor internals</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2560">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PressureSensingProcess"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b698">
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b699"/>
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b694"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b424">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/EnclosureFunction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/StructuralForce">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">structural force</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">força estrutural</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/AlternatingElectricalCurrent">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">alternating electrical current</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">corrente alternado elétrico</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/MountingStructure">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">estrutura de suporte de montagem</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">mounting structure</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000101">
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000101"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions for this constructive type because under OWA, any equipment with a centrifugal impeller could be incorrectly classified as a standard centrifugal compressor, including specialized hybrid equipment or multi-stage systems that contain centrifugal elements but should not be forced into this maintenance category. Domain expert validation needed to confirm structural differentia is sufficient.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">centrifugal compressor</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">compressor centrífugo</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A centrifugal compressor is a compressor that uses one or more centrifugal impellers to accelerate gas through radial flow and generate pressure increase by centrifugal action.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um compressor centrífugo é um compressor que usa um ou mais impelidores centrífugos para acelerar o gás através de fluxo radial e gerar aumento de pressão por ação centrífuga.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A dynamic compressor in which one ore more impellers accelerate the gas and where the main flow through the impeller is radial.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A dynamic compressor in which one ore more impellers accelerate the gas and where the main flow through the impeller is radial.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CENTRIFUGAL COMPRESSOR&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;COMPRESSOR&gt; in which one ore more impellers accelerate the gas and where the main flow through the impeller is radial, and generates pressure increase by means of centrifugal action and a volute or diffuser casing.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every centrifugal compressor is a compressor that has component part at all times some centrifugal impeller and participates in some radial flow pattern.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000073"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b419"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b418"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (CentrifugalCompressor(x) → Compressor(x) ∧ ∃i(CentrifugalImpeller(i) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,i)) ∧ ∃p(RadialFlowPattern(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/InjectionFunction">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1987"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1976"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1986"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1977"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/DesignedFunction"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de injeção</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">injection function</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1488">
    <rdf:first rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000127"/>
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1489"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000226">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">check valve body</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">corpo de válvula</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(CheckValveBody(x) → ValveBody(x) ∧ ∃y(CheckValve(y) ∧ designedFor(x,y)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000078"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b465"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive identity based on structural design for check valve accommodation. Under OWA, any housing designed for check valves could include specialized configurations, custom manifolds, or hybrid designs that should not be automatically classified as standard check valve bodies without domain expert validation of the structural differentia.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">CheckValveBody subClassOf ValveBody and (designedFor some CheckValve)</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um corpo de válvula que é especificamente projetado para acomodar e alojar os mecanismos internos de uma válvula de retenção dentro de uma barreira de contenção de pressão.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A valve body that is specifically designed to accommodate and house the internal mechanisms of a check valve within a pressure-containing boundary.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CHECK VALVE BODY&gt; is a &lt;VALVE BODY&gt; of a check valve</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000344">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A scraper is a material artifact that bears a scraping function for mechanically removing deposits, debris, or contaminants from surfaces.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um raspador é um artefato material que possui uma função de raspagem para remover mecanicamente depósitos, detritos ou contaminantes de superfícies.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every scraper is a material artifact that has a scraping function, and every material artifact that has a scraping function is a scraper.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object intended to mechanically remove a deposit from a surface.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SCRAPER&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that is capable of &lt;SCRAPING&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] Also called a pig, a device with blades or brushes inserted in a pipeline for cleaning purposes.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A device that cuts through paraffin, asphaltenes, etc. inside the pipe. Run on wireline.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Scraper(x) ↔ (MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃f(ScrapingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">raspador</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">scraper</rdfs:label>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2804"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b748">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/DampingProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2229">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/MechanicalEnergyGenerationProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
