    <owl:intersectionOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2708"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3014">
    <rdf:first rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000158"/>
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3015"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1823">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/SolidStorageAndDispensingFunction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/VisualInspectionFunction">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2921"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2920"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000029"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in a VisualInspectionProcess and that consists in enabling direct optical observation of internal conditions, fluid properties, or process states within containers, vessels, or piping systems for operational monitoring, safety verification, or maintenance purposes.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de inspeção visual</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">visual inspection function</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000120">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A type of valve that incorporates a sliding gate to block fluid flow.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A valve with a sliding bar – common in the oilfield as tree valves.                  Gate valve is defined in API SPEC 6A as a valve assembly with a closure mechanism operating within the body, 90° to the conduit, to affect a closure. Gate valves are commonly used in the wellhead section of the well either as a side outlet valve in the spools or in the Christmas tree.                  Gate valves have two modes, either fully open or fully closed. This distinguish the gate valve from the chole valve. The gate valve will allow the fluid to follow or it will completely stop it. On the other hand, a choke valve will restrict the flow.                  Gate valves have several components including but not limited to:                  * Gate                  * Seat                  * Stem                  * Stem Packing (Seal)                  * Bearings                  * Grease fitting                  * Studs and nuts                  * Hand wheel</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A valve that is a valve where the closure member is a gate or disc with a linear motion parallel, or nearly parallel, to the plane of flat seats, which are transverse to the direction of flow.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A valve that is a valve where the closure member is a gate or disc with a linear motion parallel, or nearly parallel, to the plane of flat seats, which are transverse to the direction of flow.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;GATE VALVE&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;VALVE&gt; that is a valve where the closure member is a gate or disc with a linear motion parallel, or nearly parallel, to the plane of flat seats, which are transverse to the direction of flow</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A gate valve is a valve that has a gate or disc closure member with linear motion parallel to the plane of flat seats, which are transverse to the direction of flow.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula gaveta é uma válvula que possui um membro de fechamento tipo gaveta ou disco com movimento linear paralelo ao plano dos assentos planos, que são transversais à direção do fluxo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (GateValve(x) → (Valve(x) ∧ ∃g(GateClosure(g) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,g)) ∧ ∃m(LinearActuationMechanism(m) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,m))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula gaveta</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">gate valve</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive classification based on physical mechanism. Under OWA, defining sufficient conditions for structural features like 'linear sliding gate' risks false positives from complex hybrid equipment or custom manifolds that contain gate mechanisms but should not be classified as standard gate valves. Necessary conditions provide safer classification that can be validated by domain experts.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1687"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1686"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000077"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every gate valve is a valve that has a gate closure component and a linear actuation mechanism.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/DischargePort">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">bocal de descarga</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">discharge port</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ForceReceivingElement">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">force receiving element</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">elemento de força de receptor</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000288">
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(GearCasing(x) → casing(x) ∧ ∃y(GearMechanism(y) ∧ hasContent(x,y)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">GearCasing ⊑ casing ⊓ ∃hasContent.GearMechanism</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">This is a constructive type defined by its physical configuration as a specific type of casing. Under OWA, declaring equivalence could lead to over-classification where any casing containing gear-like components might be inappropriately classified as a standard gear casing, including custom enclosures or hybrid systems that should not fall into this maintenance category.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;GEAR CASING&gt; is a &lt;HOUSING&gt; that contains the internal components of a gear.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A casing that contains and houses the internal components of a gear mechanism, providing protective enclosure and structural support.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um invólucro que contém e abriga os componentes internos de um mecanismo de engrenagem, fornecendo invólucro protetor e suporte estrutural.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1699"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000222"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">carcaça de caixa de engrenagens</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">gear casing</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000170">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">subsurface safety function</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de segurança subsuperficial</rdfs:label>
