  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000338">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that can be any electrical device, usually incorporating an electromagnet, whereby a current or signal in one circuit can open or close another circuit.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;RELAY&gt; is a &lt;SWITCHING DEVICE&gt; that usually is incorporating an electromagnet, whereby a current or signal in one circuit can open or close another circuit</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[isa5_1] a device, whose function is to pass on information in an unchanged form or in some modified form, often used to mean the preferred term computing device.</skos:definition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2688"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every Relay is an ElectricalSwitchingDevice that bearerOf some SignalRelayFunction</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">relay</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">relé</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A relay is an electrical switching device that bears a signal relay function, realized by passing on information or signals from one circuit to control operations in another circuit.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um relé é um dispositivo de comutação elétrica que possui uma função de relé de sinal, realizada ao transmitir informações ou sinais de um circuito para controlar operações em outro circuito.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Relay(x) ↔ (ElectricalSwitchingDevice(x) ∧ ∃f(SignalRelayFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3037">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/BackflowPreventionProcess"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1526">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FlowModificationFunction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2724">
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2725"/>
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2721"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000346">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um Assembly que porta uma PowerTransmissionFunction e que possui partes componentes incluindo chavetas de eixo para transmissão de torque e vedações de eixo para prevenção de vazamento, servindo como o elemento rotativo central em máquinas rotativas.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An Assembly that bears a PowerTransmissionFunction and that has component parts including shaft keys for torque transmission and shaft seals for leakage prevention, serving as the core rotating element in rotating machinery.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive classification based on physical structure. Under OWA, sufficient conditions for shaft identity could lead to false positives - any assembly with a shaft key and rotational motion might be classified as a shaft rather than a more specific equipment type that contains a shaft. The structural differentia provides necessary conditions while allowing domain experts to validate sufficiency.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">shaft</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">eixo</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2872"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2871"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2873"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2874"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Shaft(x) → Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(PowerTransmissionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃k(ShaftKey(k) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,k)) ∧ ∃s(ShaftSeal(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)) ∧ ∃l(ShaftSleeve(l) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,l)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every shaft is an assembly that transmits power through rotation and has shaft keys, shaft seals, and shaft sleeves as essential components.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SHAFT&gt; is an &lt;ENGINE COMPONENT&gt; that is the core rotating element on which the rotating parts are mounted and through which energy is either transmitted from the prime mover or generated in case of a driver.</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000271">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um arrestador de chama é um dispositivo de segurança que possui uma função de arrestar chama para prevenir que chamas entrem em um sistema através de uma abertura.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A flame arrestor is a safety device that bears a flame arrest function to prevent flames from entering a system through an opening.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flame arrestor</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">arrestador de chama</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] An arrestor which is a trap over an opening, e.g. of a ventilation system or a pipe, to prevent flames from entering the system.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FLAME ARRESTOR&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and an &lt;ARRESTOR&gt; that is a trap covering an opening, e.g of a ventilation system or a pipe, to prevent flames from entering the system</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every flame arrestor is a safety device that has the function of arresting flames and processes gaseous portions while preventing flame propagation.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(FlameArrestor(x) ↔ SafetyDevice(x) ∧ ∃f(FlameArrestFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1350"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000147">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula de segurança e alívio é uma válvula que possui uma função de alívio de segurança que combina capacidades de proteção de segurança e alívio de pressão.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A safety relief valve is a valve that bears a safety relief function combining both safety protection and pressure relief capabilities.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2782"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula de segurança e alívio</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">safety relief valve</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every safety relief valve is a valve that has the function of providing both safety protection and pressure relief.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SAFETY RELIEF VALVE&gt; is a &lt;SAFETY VALVE&gt; and a &lt;RELIEF VALVE&gt;</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(SafetyReliefValve(x) ↔ (Valve(x) ∧ ∃f(SafetyReliefFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/CondensationSurface">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">superfície de condensação</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">condensation surface</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000296">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A tubular which is flexible and capable of conveying liquids under pressure.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;HOSE&gt; is a &lt;TUBULAR&gt; that is flexible and capable of conducting liquids under pressure</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A tubular which is flexible and capable of conveying liquids under pressure.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Hose(x) → Pipe(x) ∧ ∃q(Flexibility(q) ∧ hasQuality(x,q)) ∧ ∃c(PressurizedFluidConduction(c) ∧ capableOf(x,c)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma mangueira é um tubo flexível projetado para conduzir líquidos sob pressão enquanto acomoda movimento posicional e flexão.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A hose is a flexible pipe designed to conduct liquids under pressure while accommodating positional movement and bending.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1835"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1837"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1834"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000321"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1836"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions because this is a constructive type defined by physical properties (flexibility). Under OWA, asserting equivalence would force any artifact with flexibility and pressure capability to be classified as a hose, potentially including complex equipment with flexible components that should not be categorized as standard hoses.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">mangueira</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">hose</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every hose is a pipe that has flexibility and is capable of conducting liquids under pressure.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000211">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um ValveBody que possui uma geometria de caminho de fluxo interno onde os eixos de entrada e saída são posicionados em ângulo um em relação ao outro, criando uma configuração de fluxo em formato de L ou angular.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A ValveBody that has an internal flow path geometry where the inlet and outlet axes are positioned at an angle to each other, creating an L-shaped or angled flow configuration.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b114"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000078"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (AngleValveBody(x) → ValveBody(x) ∧ ∃g (AngularFlowPath(g) ∧ hasGeometry(x,g)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type based on geometric configuration. Under OWA, sufficient conditions for geometric characteristics like 'angular flow path' are difficult to specify precisely without detailed geometric constraints that could lead to false classification of complex multi-path valve bodies or hybrid designs.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">angle valve body</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">corpo de válvula angular</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;ANGLE VALVE BODY&gt; is a &lt;VALVE BODY&gt; of an angle valve</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">AngleValveBody subClassOf ValveBody and hasGeometry some AngularFlowPath</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/SignalProcessingUnit">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ElectronicComponent"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">signal processing unit</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">unidade de sinal de processamento</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2723">
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2724"/>
    <rdf:first rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000083"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000172">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000028"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2064"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2065"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2083"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2082"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de indicação de nível</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">level indication function</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2547">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000199"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2604">
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2605"/>
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2598"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b9">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/AbsorptionProcess"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000090">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um vaso de pressão é um vaso que possui uma função de contenção sob pressão, projetado para suportar com segurança cargas de pressão internas e/ou externas.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A pressure vessel is a vessel that bears a pressure containment function, designed to safely withstand internal and/or external pressure loads.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2638"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every pressure vessel is a vessel that has a pressure containment function, and every vessel with a pressure containment function is a pressure vessel.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (PressureVessel(x) ↔ (Vessel(x) ∧ ∃f (PressureContainmentFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pressure vessel</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">vaso de pressão</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A vessel intended to withstand external and/or internal pressure</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000337">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">reciprocating pump</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">bomba alternativa</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A piston pump.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A type of fluid pump in which reciprocating pistons or plungers displace the fluid.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;RECIPROCATING PUMP&gt; is a &lt;POSITIVE DISPLACEMENT PUMP&gt; which contains a displacing element intended to be moved in a reciprocating movement to exert pressure on a fluid, typically moving within a cylindrical space.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] a positive displacement pump which contains a displacing element intended to be moved in a reciprocating movement to exert pressure on a fluid, typically moving within a cylindrical space.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A positive displacement pump which contains a displacing element intended to be moved in a reciprocating movement to exert pressure on a fluid, typically moving within a cylindrical space.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every reciprocating pump is a pump that has as component part at all times a reciprocating displacement mechanism and has as component part at all times pistons or plungers and has as component part at all times cylindrical chambers.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma bomba alternativa é uma bomba que contém pistões ou êmbolos projetados para se moverem em movimento alternativo dentro de câmaras cilíndricas para deslocar fluido através de ação de deslocamento positivo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A reciprocating pump is a pump that contains pistons or plungers designed to move in a reciprocating motion within cylindrical chambers to displace fluid through positive displacement action.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2676"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2674"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2673"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2677"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2672"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2675"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000072"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(ReciprocatingPump(x) → Pump(x) ∧ ∃m(ReciprocatingDisplacementMechanism(m) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,m)) ∧ ∃p(PistonOrPlunger(p) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,p)) ∧ ∃c(CylindricalChamber(c) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,c)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions for this constructive type. Under Open World Assumption, asserting equivalence based on structural differentia could lead to false positives where complex equipment containing reciprocating elements (like reciprocating compressors with auxiliary pumps, or hybrid systems) might be incorrectly classified as standard reciprocating pumps. The structural mechanism is necessary but sufficient conditions require domain expert validation.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
