  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/AirFinSystem">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">sistema de ar de aleta</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">air fin system</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000105">
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b490"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A valve that can be used to obstruct the fluid passing inside, and has the ability to reduce the pressure from the inlet port to the outlet port.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A valve that can be used to obstruct the fluid passing inside, and has the ability to reduce the pressure from the inlet port to the outlet port.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CHOKE VALVE&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;VALVE&gt; in which a solid cylinder is raised and lowered, and which is placed around or inside another cylinder that has holes or slots. The design of a choke valve means fluids flowing through the cage are coming from all sides and that the streams of flow (through the holes or slots) collide with each other at the center of the cage cylinder, thereby dissipating the energy of the fluid through flow impingement. The main advantage of choke valves is that they can be designed to be totally linear in their flow rate</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">choke valve</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula choke</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula choke é uma válvula que possui uma função de redução de pressão, projetada para reduzir a pressão do fluido da entrada para a saída através de restrição controlada do fluxo e dissipação de energia.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A choke valve is a valve that bears a pressure reduction function, designed to reduce fluid pressure from inlet to outlet through controlled flow restriction and energy dissipation.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (ChokeValve(x) ↔ (Valve(x) ∧ ∃f (PressureReductionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every choke valve is a valve that bears a pressure reduction function and has a flow restriction element as component part at all times.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000105"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b803">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/DehumidificationProcess"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1602">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/SeparationProcess"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3042">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000371"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/Cavity">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">cavity</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">cavidade</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000335">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A casing that surrounds an impeller and has integral suction and discharge nozzles as structural components, typically applied in centrifugal pumps.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um invólucro que envolve um impulsor e possui bocais de sucção e descarga integrais como componentes estruturais, tipicamente aplicado em bombas centrífugas.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2662"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000222"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">carcaça de bomba</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pump casing</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;PUMP CASING&gt; is a  &lt;CASING&gt; and a single wall surrounding the impeller. The suction and discharge nozzles form an integral part of the casing. Typically applied for centrifugal pumps</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type based on physical configuration. Under Open World Assumption, structural characteristics are harder to make sufficient - any assembly with an impeller and integral nozzles might be classified as a pump casing even if it serves a different specialized purpose. Starting with necessary conditions protects against false positives.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(PumpCasing(x) → Casing(x) ∧ ∃y(Impeller(y) ∧ surrounds(x,y)) ∧ ∃z(SuctionNozzle(z) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,z)) ∧ ∃w(DischargeNozzle(w) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,w)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every pump casing is a casing that surrounds an impeller and has integral suction and discharge nozzles forming part of its structure.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000326">
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Pipeline(x) ↔ EngineeredSystem(x) ∧ ∃f(FluidTransportFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A fluid conductor that consists of pipe, possibly also including pumps, valves, and control devices, intended for conveying liquids, gases, or finely divided solids.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;PIPELINE&gt; is a &lt;CONTINOUS FLUID TRANSPORTER&gt; and a &lt;FLUID CONDUCTOR&gt; and a &lt;SYSTEM&gt; that consists of pipe, possibly also including pumps, valves, and control devices, intended for conveying liquids, gases, or finely divided solids</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A tube or system of tubes used for transporting crude oil and natural gas from the field or gathering system to the refinery.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A fluid conductor that consists of pipe, possibly also including pumps, valves, and control devices, intended for conveying liquids, gases, or finely divided solids.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] The principle underground transport of produced gas and oil.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every pipeline is an engineered system that bears a fluid transport function and has pipe as a component part at some time.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pipeline</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">pipeline</rdfs:label>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2428"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um pipeline é um sistema engenheirado que possui uma função de transporte de fluidos, consistindo de tubos e possivelmente incluindo bombas, válvulas e dispositivos de controle, projetado para transportar líquidos, gases ou sólidos finamente divididos entre locais.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A pipeline is an engineered system that bears a fluid transport function, consisting of pipes and possibly including pumps, valves, and control devices, designed for conveying liquids, gases, or finely divided solids between locations.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b137">
    <rdf:first rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000157"/>
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b138"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000375">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A well is an engineered system that interacts with subsurface resources through a drilled wellbore, designed to obtain, produce, store, or inject materials into or from the earth.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um poço é um sistema projetado que interage com recursos do subsolo através de um furo perfurado, projetado para obter, produzir, armazenar ou injetar materiais na terra ou a partir dela.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ppdm] A Well is a permitted or actual drilled hole in the ground designed to exchange (or facilitate the exchange of) fluids between a subsurface reservoir and the surface (or another reservoir), or to enable the detection and measurement of rock properties. Key concept: A physical Well is created each time the drill bit breaks the surface of the earth. Clarification: A Well is the parent of the Wellhead Stream(s), Well Origin, and all Well Components down hole from its Well Origin. A Well has a single Well Origin and all Wellbore(s) that extend from this Well Origin are parts of the Well. Re-entry through the same Well Origin for a Well that has not been plugged and abandoned does not create a new Well. A Well that has the same geographic coordinates as a previously existing plugged and abandoned, reclaimed or undrilled Well is a new Well. WB2-Cl2 Diagram Note: The Well depicted on page 3 groups multiple Well Components, including: one active Well WB2-C1 Origin (WO1), one inactive Wellbore (WB1), two active Wellbores (WB2, WB3), three inactive Wellbore Completions (WB1-C1, WB1-C2, WB1-C3) and three active Wellbore Completions (WB2-C1, WB3-C1, WB3-C2) and two active Wellbore Contact Intervals (WB2- CI1, WB2-CI2). ® Copyright 2014, PPDM Association. All Rights Reserved PAGE 4</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;WELL&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that is arranged to obtain or produce from, or store or inject a material into, the earth</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A well is a collection of (zero or more) holes drilled into the Earth for the purpose of either (1) finding or producing underground resources; or (2) providing services related to the production of underground resources.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">well</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">poço</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Well(x) ↔ EngineeredSystem(x) ∧ ∃f(SubsurfaceResourceInteractionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃w(Wellbore(w) ∧ hasComponentPartAtSomeTime(x,w)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3408"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every well is an engineered system that bears a subsurface resource interaction function and has a wellbore as component part.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000148">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula de segurança</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">safety valve</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A quick-opening, pop-action valve used for fast relief of excessive pressure.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] Various. Generally used in describing a surface or subsurface safety valve.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SAFETY VALVE&gt; is an &lt;INSTRUMENTATION ITEM&gt; and a &lt;PRESSURE RELIEF DEVICE&gt; that is used in gas service</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula de segurança é uma válvula que possui uma função de ventilação de segurança para alívio automático de pressão por abertura rápida e total para proteção contra condições perigosas de sobrepressão.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A safety valve is a valve that bears a safety venting function for automatic pressure relief through rapid full opening to protect against dangerous overpressure conditions.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every safety valve is a valve that has the function to automatically relieve excess pressure for emergency protection</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2792"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(SafetyValve(x) ↔ Valve(x) ∧ ∃f(SafetyReliefFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2544">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ElectricalPowerTransformationProcess"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000098">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b275"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b273"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b274"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000073"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b276"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A physical object intended to compress and supply air or gas at medium pressure and medium volume flow.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object intended to compress and supply air or gas at medium pressure and medium volume flow.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;BLOWER&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that is capable of &lt;BLOWING&gt; a medium volume flow</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">soprador</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">blower</rdfs:label>
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000098"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Blower(x) ↔ (Compressor(x) ∧ ∃f,p,v (CompressionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f) ∧ MediumPressureRange(p) ∧ MediumVolumeFlowRange(v) ∧ hasOperatingParameter(x,p) ∧ hasOperatingParameter(x,v))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every blower is a compressor that has the function of compressing gas and operates at medium pressure and medium volume flow ranges.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um soprador é um compressor que comprime e fornece ar ou gás em pressão média e vazão volumétrica média.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A blower is a compressor that compresses and supplies air or gas at medium pressure and medium volume flow.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FluidTransportFunction">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2425"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1563"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1562"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2424"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/DesignedFunction"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">fluid transport function</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de transporte de fluido</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000323">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">cotovelo de tubulação</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pipe elbow</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000321"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2396"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2397"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2398"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every pipe elbow is a pipe that has curved geometry and enables directional change capacity between 0 and 135 degrees.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um cotovelo de tubulação é uma tubulação que possui geometria curva permitindo mudanças direcionais em trechos de tubulação entre 0 e 135 graus.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A pipe elbow is a pipe that has curved geometry enabling directional changes in pipe runs between 0 and 135 degrees.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] An 'elbow' and an 'artefact' that is intended to make a change in the direction of a pipe run between 0 and 135 degrees.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;PIPE ELBOW&gt; is a &lt;PIPING COMPONENT&gt; and an &lt;ELBOW&gt; that is intended to make a change in the direction of a pipe run between 0 and 135 degrees</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions for this constructive type protects against false positives under OWA. Any curved piping component would be forcibly classified as a pipe elbow under equivalent axioms, including specialized equipment like coiled tubing, serpentine heat exchanger tubes, or custom manifold sections that contain curved passages but should not be asserted into the standard pipe elbow maintenance category.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (PipeElbow(x) → (Pipe(x) ∧ ∃g(CurvedGeometry(g) ∧ hasGeometricProperty(x,g)) ∧ ∃p(DirectionalChangeCapacity(p) ∧ hasProperty(x,p))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/VisualInformation">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">informação visual</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">visual information</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ExhaustStack">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">chaminé de escapamento</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">exhaust stack</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1977">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/InjectionProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000188">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3106"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3107"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/DesignedFunction"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">temperature measurement and transmission function</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de medição e transmissão de temperatura</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1871">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/HydraulicFluidPort"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000367">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">umbilical</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">umbilical</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3274"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3275"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3277"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3273"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3276"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive basis requires necessary conditions only. Under OWA, any assembly with cables, tubing, flexibility, and disconnectability could be forcibly classified as umbilical, including specialized multi-service bundles, complex wiring harnesses, or custom transmission assemblies that contain these elements but serve different industrial contexts and maintenance categories.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] An assembly of hydraulic hoses which can also include electrical cables or optic fibres, used to control a sub sea structure or remote operated vehicle from a platform or a vessel.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;UMBILICAL&gt; is a &lt;DRILLING COMPONENT&gt; that is a flexible and easily disconnectable collection of cables and/or tubing for control, power, communication or chemical injection purposes.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A control line attached to a remove piece of equipment, usually a subsea wellhead, to provide hydraulic or electrical control, or inject small amounts of chemicals.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A device which is a flexible and easily disconnectable collection of cables and/or tubing for control, power, communication or chemical injection purposes.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every umbilical is an assembly that has component parts including cable bundles and tubing bundles, and has the qualities of flexibility and easy disconnectability.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um umbilical é uma montagem que é um feixe flexível e facilmente desconectável contendo cabos e tubulação para transmissão de múltiplos serviços incluindo controle, energia, comunicação e injeção química.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An umbilical is an assembly that is a flexible and easily disconnectable bundle containing both cables and tubing for multi-service transmission including control, power, communication, and chemical injection.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Umbilical(x) → Assembly(x) ∧ ∃c,t,s,conn (CableBundle(c) ∧ TubingBundle(t) ∧ ProtectiveSheathing(s) ∧ ConnectorAssembly(conn) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,c) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,t) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,conn) ∧ hasQuality(x,Flexibility) ∧ hasQuality(x,EasyDisconnectability)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000349">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma polia é um artefato material que é uma roda sulcada projetada para transmitir energia mecânica através da interface com correias, cordas, cabos ou tubos.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A sheave is a material artifact that is a grooved wheel designed to transmit mechanical power through interface with belts, ropes, wires, or pipes.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">sheave</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">polia</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] In oilfield usage, the term usually refers to either the pulleys permanently mounted on the top of the rig (the crown blocks), or the pulleys used for running wireline tools into the wellbore.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A wheel which is grooved for use with vee-belts, ropes, round belts, wire or pipe.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SHEAVE&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;WHEEL&gt; which is grooved for use with vee-belts, ropes, round belts, wire or pipe</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A grooved pulley.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type based on physical structure. Under OWA, defining sufficient conditions based solely on having a grooved rim could lead to false positives where other grooved mechanical elements (like timing belt pulleys with different design intents) are automatically classified as sheaves. The structural differentia provides necessary conditions while allowing domain experts to confirm sufficient conditions.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2908"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2907"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2906"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Sheave(x) → MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃y(GroovedRim(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y)) ∧ ∃f(PowerTransmissionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every sheave is a material artifact that has a grooved rim as component part and bears a power transmission function.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
