  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000272">
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every flame detector is a detector that has a flame detection function, and every detector that has a flame detection function is a flame detector.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">detector de chama</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flame detector</rdfs:label>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1365"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A detector that is intended to sense a flame.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FLAME DETECTOR&gt; is a &lt;DETECTOR&gt; and a &lt;FLAME DETECTING INSTRUMENT&gt; using a &lt;FLAME DETECTING MEASURING ELEMENT&gt; that is designed to detect the presence of a flame</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A detector that is intended to sense a flame.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A flame detector is a detector that has the function to detect the presence of flames.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um detector de chama é um detector que tem a função de detectar a presença de chamas.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(FlameDetector(x) ↔ Detector(x) ∧ ∃f(FlameDetectionFunction(f) ∧ hasFunction(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ElectromagneticRadiation">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">radiação eletromagnético</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">electromagnetic radiation</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000327">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2476"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2473"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000207"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2475"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2474"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">atuador pneumático</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pneumatic actuator</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] An actuator that is intended to be operated by pneumatic power.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] An actuator that is intended to be operated by pneumatic power.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;PNEUMATIC ACTUATOR&gt; is an &lt;INSTRUMENTATION ITEM&gt; and a &lt;CONTROLLED ACTUATOR&gt; that is intended to be operated by pneumatic power</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type where pneumatic mechanism is necessary but may not be sufficient under OWA. Specialized pneumatic equipment (pneumatic tools, pneumatic cylinders) might have pneumatic power but should not be classified as actuators without additional validation of their actuation role in control systems.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um atuador pneumático é um atuador que opera usando energia pneumática.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A pneumatic actuator is an actuator that operates using pneumatic power.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(PneumaticActuator(x) → Actuator(x) ∧ ∃y(PneumaticPower(y) ∧ hasOperatingMedium(x,y)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every pneumatic actuator is an actuator that has operating medium some pneumatic power.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000321">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A pipe is a material artifact characterized by tubular geometry and longitudinal extent, designed to conduct liquid, gaseous or finely divided solid materials from one location to another, or to serve structural purposes.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um tubo é um artefato material caracterizado por geometria tubular e extensão longitudinal, projetado para conduzir materiais líquidos, gasosos ou sólidos finamente divididos de um local para outro, ou para servir a propósitos estruturais.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">tubo</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pipe</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that is a long tube or hollow body intended for conduction of liquid, gaseous or finely divided solid materials, or used for structural purposes.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;PIPE&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;FLUID CONDUCTOR&gt; that is a long tube or hollow body intended for conduction of liquid, gaseous or finely divided solid materials, or used for structural purposes</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[DEXPI] An elementary piece of piping, i.e., not interrupted by any item.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] An 'artefact' that is a long tube or hollow body intended for conduction of liquid, gaseous or finely divided solid materials, or used for structural purposes.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2375"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2374"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2376"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions because pipe is defined by constructive/geometric properties (tubular geometry, longitudinal extent) rather than purely functional criteria. Under Open World Assumption, asserting sufficient conditions based on geometric properties could lead to unintended classification of complex tubular structures that happen to conduct fluids but should not be categorized as standard pipes.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Pipe(x) → MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃f(FluidConductionFunction(f) ∧ hasFunction(x,f)) ∧ ∃g(TubularGeometry(g) ∧ hasPhysicalProperty(x,g)) ∧ ∃h(LongitudinalExtent(h) ∧ hasPhysicalProperty(x,h)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every pipe is a material artifact that has fluid conduction function and has tubular geometry and has longitudinal extent.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000084">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A production treating vessel designed to facilitate the separation of gas, oil, and/or water from a produced fluid stream.                  Also                  The term separator in oilfield terminology designates a pressure vessel used for separating well fluids produced from oil and gas wells into gaseous and liquid components. A separator for petroleum production is a large vessel designed to separate production fluids into their constituent components of oil, gas and water. Separators include related process control components, like pneumatic controllers, and may contain a heater to enhance phase separation or prevent freezing during cold weather. A separating vessel may be referred to in the following ways: Oil and gas separator, Separator, Stage separator, Trap, Knockout vessel (Knockout drum, knockout trap, water knockout, or liquid knockout), Flash chamber (flash vessel or flash trap), Expansion separator or expansion vessel, Scrubber (gas scrubber), Filter (gas filter). These separating vessels are normally used on a producing lease or platform near the wellhead, manifold, or tank battery to separate fluids produced from oil and gas wells into oil and gas or liquid and gas. https://www.mines.edu/global-energy-future/wp-content/uploads/sites/361/2024/05/Payne_Institute_Responsible_Gas_Glossary_of_Terminology_211022_version-9.pdf</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A cylindrical or spherical vessel used to separate oil, gas and water from the total fluid stream produced by a well. Separators can be either horizontal or vertical.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A 'device' intended to separate different types of substances.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SEPARATOR&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that has a capability of &lt;SEPARATING&gt;</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">separator</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">separador</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um separador é um vaso que possui uma FunçãoDeSeparação - projetado para separar diferentes substâncias ou fases de uma corrente fluida mista em correntes de saída distintas.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A separator is a vessel that bears a SeparationFunction - designed to separate different substances or phases from a mixed fluid stream into distinct output streams.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every separator is a vessel that has the function of separating mixed fluid streams into distinct phases or components.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Separator(x) ↔ (Vessel(x) ∧ ∃f (SeparationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2851"/>
  </rdf:Description>
