  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000355">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um MaterialArtifact que possui uma StationaryMachineComponentFunction e que é o componente estrutural estacionário dentro de máquinas rotativas, fornecendo alojamento e estabilidade posicional para elementos ativos como bobinas, palhetas ou vedações.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A MaterialArtifact that bears a StationaryMachineComponentFunction and that is the stationary structural component within rotating machinery, providing housing and positional stability for active elements such as windings, vanes, or seals.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3006"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3007"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Stator(x) → MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃f(StationaryMachineComponentFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃m(RotatingMachine(m) ∧ partOf(x,m)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every Stator is a MaterialArtifact that bears a StationaryMachineComponentFunction and is part of some RotatingMachine</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] In the context of a PDM motor, a stator is the stationary rubber element of a PDM motor.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;STATOR&gt; is a &lt;MACHINE COMPONENT&gt; that is the arrangement of primary coils being the stator winding and being the stationary part of a machine</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">stator</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">MaterialArtifact que possui uma StationaryMachineComponentFunction e</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive classification based on structural positioning within rotating machinery. Under OWA, any artifact described as stationary within a rotating machine context could be classified as a stator, but this may include specialized hybrid components, mounting structures, or custom configurations that should not be automatically asserted into the standard stator maintenance category. The structural differentia (stationary positioning) is necessary but making it sufficient requires domain expert validation.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000096">
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(BlockAndBleedValve(x) → Valve(x) ∧ ∃s(SingleSeat(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)) ∧ ∃l(BleederLine(l) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,l)) ∧ ∃v(BleederValve(v) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,v)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">block and bleed valve</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula de bloqueio e sangria</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b257"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000077"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula de bloqueio e sangria é uma válvula que possui um assento que fornece vedação, e uma linha de sangria e válvula que são conectadas ao castelo da válvula para ventilação controlada da pressão a jusante.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A block and bleed valve is a valve that has one seat which provides a seal, and a bleeder line and valve that are tapped into the valve bonnet for controlled venting of downstream pressure.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;BLOCK AND BLEED VALVE&gt; is a &lt;BLOCK VALVE&gt; and a &lt;BLEED VALVE&gt; that has one seat which provides a seal, and a bleeder line and valve that are tapped into the block valves bonnet</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A valve that has one seat which provides a seal, and a bleeder line and valve that are tapped into the block valve's bonnet.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive types require necessary conditions only due to Open World Assumption. The structural differentia (single seat + bleeder system) could theoretically be present in specialized equipment that should not be classified as a standard block and bleed valve without domain expert validation.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every block and bleed valve is a valve that has component parts: exactly one seat, a bleeder line, and a bleeder valve integrated into the bonnet.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000163">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/DesignedFunction"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2717"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2716"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flow restriction function</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de restrição de fluxo</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000106">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A circuit breaker is a material artifact that bears an electrical current interruption function and regularly participates in processes that safely interrupt electrical current.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um disjuntor é um equipamento elétrico que possui uma função de proteção de circuito e participa em processos de interrupção de corrente em intervalos regulares.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um disjuntor é um dispositivo de chaveamento elétrico que possui uma função de interrupção de corrente elétrica e participa regularmente em processos que interrompem com segurança a corrente elétrica.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A circuit-breaker is an electrical equipment that bears a circuit protection function and participates in current interruption processes at regular intervals.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000106"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">disjuntor</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">circuit breaker</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (CircuitBreaker(x) ↔ ElectricalSwitchingDevice(x) ∧ ∃f (ElectricalCurrentInterruptionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃p (RegularInterruptionProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(CircuitBreaker(x) ↔ ElectricalEquipment(x) ∧ ∃f(CircuitProtectionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃p(CurrentInterruptionProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CIRCUIT BREAKER&gt; is an &lt;ELECTRICAL APPARATUS&gt; and a &lt;SWITCHING DEVICE&gt; that at regular intervals interrupts an electric current</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A mechanical switching device that at regular intervals interrupts an electric current.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A mechanical switching device that at regular intervals interrupts an electric current.</skos:definition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b544"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b552"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every circuit-breaker is an electrical equipment that has the function to protect circuits and participates in the process of interrupting electrical current at regular intervals.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every circuit breaker is an electrical switching device that has the function to interrupt electrical current and participates in regular current interruption processes.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000325">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2419"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2418"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2420"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000321"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2417"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">tê de tubulação</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pipe tee</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every pipe tee is a pipe that has exactly three fluid ports arranged in T-configuration and bears a fluid conduction function</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(PipeTee(x) → Pipe(x) ∧ ∃p1,p2,p3(BranchPort(p1) ∧ RunPort(p2) ∧ RunPort(p3) ∧ hasPartAtAllTimes(x,p1) ∧ hasPartAtAllTimes(x,p2) ∧ hasPartAtAllTimes(x,p3) ∧ perpendicularTo(p1,p2) ∧ perpendicularTo(p1,p3)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um tê de tubulação é uma conexão de tubulação que possui três portas de fluido dispostas em configuração em formato de T, com uma porta de ramal perpendicular a duas portas de passagem, projetada para realizar função de condução de fluido através de divisão ou combinação de fluxo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A pipe tee is a pipe fitting that has three fluid ports arranged in T-shaped configuration, with one branch port perpendicular to two run ports, designed to realize fluid conduction function through flow division or combination.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;PIPE TEE&gt; is a &lt;PIPING COMPONENT&gt; and a &lt;PIPING NETWORK NODE&gt; and three piping ends in T-shape, including a branch at 90 degrees</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] An 'artefact' that has three piping ends in T-shape, including a branch at 90 degrees.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that has three piping ends in T-shape, including a branch at 90 degrees.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions for this constructive type. The T-shaped geometric configuration with three specific ports is a structural differentia that is harder to make sufficient under OWA. Custom manifolds or complex fittings might contain T-shaped passages but should not be automatically classified as standard pipe tees without domain expert validation.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
