  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000099">
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(ButterflyControlValve(x) → Valve(x) ∧ ∃d(RotatingDisc(d) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,d)) ∧ ∃a(Actuator(a) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,a)) ∧ ∃f(ProcessControlledFlowFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A butterfly control valve is a control valve that has a rotating disc closure mechanism and bears a process-controlled flow function enabling automated flow modulation in response to external control signals.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula borboleta de controle é uma válvula de controle que possui um mecanismo de fechamento por disco rotativo e possui uma função de fluxo controlado por processo, permitindo modulação automatizada do fluxo em resposta a sinais de controle externos.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;BUTTERFLY CONTROL VALVE&gt; is an &lt;INSTRUMENTATION ITEM&gt; and a &lt;CONTROL VALVE&gt; and a &lt;BUTTERFLY VALVE&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A butterfly valve that is equipped with an actuator that manipulates a stream of fluid in the response to a signal from an external sensing element and with input of energy from an external source.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b353"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b354"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000087"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b352"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">butterfly control valve</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula borboleta de controle</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">This is a constructive type that combines two existing differentia (butterfly mechanism + control function). Under OWA, providing sufficient conditions could lead to false positives where any valve with both a rotating disc and control capability would be classified as this specific type, even if it has additional specialized features or hybrid mechanisms.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every butterfly control valve is a valve that has-component-part-at-all-times some rotating disc and has-component-part-at-all-times some actuator and bearer-of some process-controlled flow function.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2182">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ActuationFunction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000360">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">thin plate</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">Placa que possui geometria de espessura fina e</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3139"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A Plate that has thin thickness geometry and is manufactured through cold forming processes, typically used for structural support applications requiring reduced weight or specific geometric constraints.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma Placa que possui geometria de espessura fina e é fabricada através de processos de conformação a frio, tipicamente usada para aplicações de suporte estrutural que requerem peso reduzido ou restrições geométricas específicas.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type defined by physical geometry (thinness) and manufacturing method (cold forming). Under OWA, sufficient conditions for thin plates are difficult to specify without risking false positives from specialized hybrid structures that contain thin cold-formed elements but should not be classified as standard thin plates.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">ThinPlate ⊑ Plate ⊓ ∃hasQuality.ThinThickness ⊓ ∃hasQuality.ColdFormedManufacturing</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(ThinPlate(x) → Plate(x) ∧ ∃q1(ThinThickness(q1) ∧ hasQuality(x,q1)) ∧ ∃q2(ColdFormedManufacturing(q2) ∧ hasQuality(x,q2)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;THIN PLATE&gt; is a &lt;PLATE&gt; that is a thin steel plate format (Sheet plate) Normally made by coldforming</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3149">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/OilOutlet"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
