  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000217">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A boiler is a heater that brings a liquid to its boiling point through indirect contact heat exchange, producing steam or vapor.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma caldeira é um aquecedor que leva um líquido ao seu ponto de ebulição através de troca de calor por contato indireto, produzindo vapor.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[DEXPI] A that brings a liquid to its boiling point.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] An indirect contact heat exchanger that is intended to heat a liquid.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;BOILER&gt; is a &lt;HEATER&gt; that brings a &lt;LIQUID&gt; to its boiling point</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">boiler</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">caldeira</rdfs:label>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b286"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Boiler(x) ↔ Heater(x) ∧ ∃f(BoilingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every boiler is a heater that bears a BoilingFunction and has component parts including a steam drum and heat exchange surface.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3274">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/CableBundle"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000378">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every wireline is an electrical cable that has the function to lower tools into wellbores and transmit logging data signals to the surface.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um wireline é um cabo elétrico que possui uma função de perfilagem wireline para descer ferramentas em poços e transmitir dados sobre as condições do poço.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A wireline is an electrical cable that bears a wireline logging function for lowering tools into wellbores and transmitting data about wellbore conditions.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">wireline</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">wireline</rdfs:label>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3451"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] Related to any aspect of logging that employs an electrical cable to lower tools into the borehole and to transmit data. Wireline logging is distinct from measurements-while-drilling (MWD) and mud logging.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;WIRELINE&gt; is an &lt;ELECTRICAL CABLE&gt; used to lower tools into and transmit data about the conditions of the wellbore called wireline logs. Usually consisting of braided cables, wirelines are used to perform wireline logging, as well.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] schlumberger wireline, well logging, well intervention, slickline, formation evaluation</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Wireline(x) ↔ ElectricalCable(x) ∧ ∃f (WirelineLoggingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b121">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/AnodeFunction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/AgitatorDrive">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">acionamento de agitador</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">agitator drive</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2742">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PumpingProcess"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000110">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um transmissor de pressão diferencial é um transmissor de pressão que possui uma função de transmissão de pressão diferencial, permitindo medir a diferença de pressão entre dois sinais de pressão de entrada e transmitir essa diferença como um sinal de saída padronizado.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A differential pressure transmitter is a pressure transmitter that bears a differential pressure transmission function, enabling it to measure the pressure difference between two input pressure signals and transmit this difference as a standardized output signal.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1018"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every differential pressure transmitter is a pressure transmitter that bears a differential pressure transmission function</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (DifferentialPressureTransmitter(x) ↔ PressureTransmitter(x) ∧ ∃f (DifferentialPressureTransmissionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A pressure transmitter that is producing a standardized output signal dependent of a received pressure difference signal.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DIFFERENTIAL PRESSURE TRANSMITTER&gt; is a &lt;PRESSURE TRANSMITTER&gt; and a &lt;DIFFERENTIAL PRESSURE MEASURING INSTRUMENT&gt;</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">differential pressure transmitter</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">transmissor de pressão diferencial</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/BottomHoleDrillingProcess">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">bottom hole drilling process</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de perfuração de fundo de poço</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b123">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ActiveMaterial"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000135">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">on off control valve</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula de controle liga-desliga</rdfs:label>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2271"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula de controle liga-desliga é uma válvula de controle que possui uma função de controle de fluxo binária, tendo apenas duas posições definidas: totalmente aberta e totalmente fechada.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An on-off control valve is a control valve that bears a binary flow control function, having only two defined positions: fully open and fully closed.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every on-off control valve is a control valve that has a BinaryFlowControlFunction and has component part a BinaryPositioner.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;ON-OFF CONTROL VALVE&gt; is an &lt;INSTRUMENTATION ITEM&gt; and a &lt;CONTROL VALVE&gt; that only has two defined positions, being fully open and fully closed</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(OnOffControlValve(x) ↔ ControlValve(x) ∧ ∃f(BinaryFlowControlFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3237">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ChristmasTreeConnectionInterface"/>
  </rdf:Description>
