  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000366">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that is intended to rotate within a fluid and to transform energy within a fluid into mechanical power.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;TURBINE&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;DRIVER(function)&gt; that is a rotary mechanical device that extracts energy from a fluid flow and converts it into useful work</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[DEXPI] An object that is a rotary mechanical device that extracts energy from a fluid flow and converts it into useful work (from ``_).</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Turbine(x) ↔ Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(EnergyExtractionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃s(RotatingShaft(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)) ∧ ∃b(FluidInteractionBlades(b) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,b)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every turbine is an assembly that bears an energy extraction function and has component parts including a rotating shaft, fluid interaction blades, casing, and bearing system.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A turbine is an assembly that bears an energy extraction function and has rotating shaft and fluid-interacting blades that extract energy from flowing fluids and convert it into useful mechanical work.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma turbina é um conjunto que possui uma função de extração de energia e tem eixo rotativo e pás de interação com fluidos que extraem energia de fluidos em movimento e a convertem em trabalho mecânico útil.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">turbine</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">turbina</rdfs:label>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3249"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000248">
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Classification basis is constructive - identity given by diaphragm mechanism. Under OWA, sufficient conditions would force any equipment with a diaphragm component to be classified as a diaphragm actuator, potentially including complex hybrid systems or custom equipment where the diaphragm serves auxiliary functions. Starting with necessary conditions protects against such false positives.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um atuador de diafragma é um atuador que utiliza um diafragma como componente essencial para converter sinais de controle em movimento mecânico ou força para operar outros equipamentos.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A diaphragm actuator is an actuator that uses a diaphragm as an essential component for converting control signals into mechanical motion or force to operate other equipment.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000207"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b925"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">DiaphragmActuator ⊑ Actuator ⊓ ∃hasComponentPartAtAllTimes.Diaphragm</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">atuador de diafragma</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">diaphragm actuator</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(DiaphragmActuator(x) → (Actuator(x) ∧ ∃y(Diaphragm(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DIAPHRAGM ACTUATOR&gt; is an &lt;INSTRUMENTATION ITEM&gt; and a &lt;CONTROLLED ACTUATOR&gt; that is using a &lt;DIAPHRAGM&gt;</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000307">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000092"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2021"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2023"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2020"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2022"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">kettle reboiler</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">refervedor tipo kettle</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type defined by specific physical configuration. Under Open World Assumption, sufficient conditions could incorrectly classify equipment with horizontal orientation and vapor space but fundamentally different purposes (e.g., horizontal separators, flash drums) as kettle reboilers. The structural differentia provides necessary conditions for the kettle reboiler maintenance/procurement category.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um refervedor tipo kettle é um refervedor que possui orientação horizontal e contém um espaço de vapor separado para desengajamento vapor-líquido.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A kettle reboiler is a reboiler that has horizontal orientation and contains a separate vapour space for vapor-liquid disengagement.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(KettleReboiler(x) → Reboiler(x) ∧ ∃q(HorizontalOrientation(q) ∧ hasQuality(x,q)) ∧ ∃v(SeparateVapourSpace(v) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,v)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every kettle reboiler is a reboiler that has horizontal orientation and has a separate vapour space as component part.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;KETTLE REBOILER&gt; is a &lt;REBOILER&gt; that is horizontal and has a separate vapour space.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A reboiler often boils liquid coming from the bottom of a distillation column, after which the resulting vapour is returned to the distillation column.</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000273">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A connection profile used in pipe work and associated equipment to provide a means of assembling and disassembling components.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FLANGE&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;CONNECTOR&gt; that is a projecting flat rim, plate, collar, or rib for strength or for attachment to another object</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A common, high pressure wellhead connection, using bolt attached flange plates and metal-to-metal seals.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that is a projecting flat rim, plate, collar or rib.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every flange is a material artifact that has a projecting flat rim geometry and has the function of mechanically connecting components.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Flange(x) → MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃g(ProjectingFlatRimGeometry(g) ∧ hasCharacteristic(x,g)) ∧ ∃f(MechanicalConnectionFunction(f) ∧ hasFunction(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1378"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1377"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1379"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um flange é um artefato material caracterizado por uma geometria de aro plano projetante, placa, colar ou nervura, projetado para fornecer conexão mecânica entre componentes.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A flange is a material artifact characterized by a projecting flat rim, plate, collar, or rib geometry, designed to provide mechanical connection between components.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flange</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">flange</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions because this is a constructive type defined by structural geometry. Under OWA, any artifact with projecting flat rim geometry would be forced into the flange category, which could incorrectly classify specialized equipment or complex assemblies that contain flange-like features but serve different primary functions.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/VaporOutlet">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">saída de vapor</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">vapor outlet</rdfs:label>
