  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000286">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;GAS TURBINE&gt; is a &lt;TURBINE&gt; that compresses air which is then mixed with fuel for combustion and expansion through a turbine section to generate relatively high power output for either mechanical drive or power generation</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A turbine that compresses air which is then mixed with fuel for combustion and expansion through a turbine section to generate relatively high power output for either mechanical drive or power generation.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A turbine that compresses air which is then mixed with fuel for combustion and expansion through a turbine section to generate relatively high power output for either mechanical drive or power generation.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">gas turbine</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">turbina a gás</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(GasTurbine(x) ↔ Turbine(x) ∧ ∃c,h(Compressor(c) ∧ CombustionChamber(h) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,c) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,h)) ∧ ∃p1,p2(AirCompressionProcess(p1) ∧ FuelCombustionProcess(p2) ∧ participatesIn(x,p1) ∧ participatesIn(x,p2)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every gas turbine is a turbine that has component parts compressor and combustion chamber at all times, and participates in air compression process and fuel combustion process.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1645"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma turbina a gás é uma turbina que possui um compressor e câmara de combustão integrados, projetada para comprimir ar ambiente, misturá-lo com combustível para combustão, e expandir os gases quentes resultantes através de uma seção de turbina para gerar energia mecânica.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A gas turbine is a turbine that has an integrated compressor and combustion chamber, designed to compress ambient air, mix it with fuel for combustion, and expand the resulting hot gases through a turbine section to generate mechanical power.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000144">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;PRESSURE TRANSMITTER&gt; is a &lt;PROCESS VARIABLE TRANSMITTER&gt; and a &lt;PRESSURE MEASURING INSTRUMENT&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A transmitter that is producing a standardized output signal dependent of a received input signal from a pressure element.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[isa5_1] ISA 5.1 tag abbreviation 'PT'. First letter 'P': Pressure. Succeeding letters: 'T' = Transmit.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every pressure transmitter is a transmitter that has the function to transmit pressure measurement signals.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A pressure transmitter is a transmitter that converts pressure measurements into standardized output signals for transmission to control or monitoring systems.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um transmissor de pressão é um transmissor que converte medições de pressão em sinais de saída padronizados para transmissão a sistemas de controle ou monitoramento.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pressure transmitter</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">transmissor de pressão</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(PressureTransmitter(x) ↔ (Transmitter(x) ∧ ∃f(PressureTransmissionFunction(f) ∧ hasFunction(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2621"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b486">
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PressureReductionProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000359">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">thermowell stem</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">termowell stem</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3136"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A thermowell stem is a fiat object part that is part of a thermowell and that has a hollow cylindrical shape positioned to protrude into the process medium, providing protective housing for temperature sensing elements while enabling thermal conduction.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um termowell stem é uma parte de objeto fiducial que é parte de um termowell e que tem uma forma cilíndrica oca posicionada para se projetar no meio do processo, fornecendo habitação protetora para elementos de detecção de temperatura enquanto permite condução térmica.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;THERMOWELL STEM&gt; is an &lt;INSTRUMENTATION ITEM&gt; and a &lt;Feature&gt; and an &lt;ENCLOSURE&gt; that is the hollow cylindrical part of a thermowell that is housing the thermocouple or thermoelement and is protruding into the process medium</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(ThermowellStem(x) → FiatObjectPart(x) ∧ ∃y(Thermowell(y) ∧ partOf(x,y)) ∧ ∃q(HollowCylindricalShape(q) ∧ hasQuality(x,q)) ∧ ∃l(ProcessMediumIntrusionZone(l) ∧ hasLocation(x,l)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive classification basis. The structural differentia (hollow cylindrical shape, positioning in process medium) is necessary but may not be sufficient under OWA - there could be other specialized parts of thermowells with similar geometry but different specific roles or configurations.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every thermowell stem is a fiat object part that is part of some thermowell and has hollow cylindrical shape and is located in process medium intrusion zone.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000287">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A seal that is one or more closed loops of deformable material used between mating surfaces which have only very limited movement relative to each other.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A seal that is one or more closed loops of deformable material used between mating surfaces which have only very limited movement relative to each other.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] Any of several replaceable seals in equipment or tools.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;GASKET&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;SEAL&gt; that is one or more closed loops of deformable material used between mating surfaces which have only very limited movement relative to each other</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma junta é um artefato material feito de material deformável arranjado em loops fechados que possui uma função de vedação para prevenir vazamentos entre superfícies de acoplamento com movimento relativo limitado.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A gasket is a material artifact made of deformable material arranged in closed loops that bears a sealing function to prevent leakage between mating surfaces with limited relative movement.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">junta</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">gasket</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Gasket(x) ↔ MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃f(SealingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃m(DeformableMaterial(m) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,m)) ∧ ∃g(ClosedLoopGeometry(g) ∧ hasProperty(x,g)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every gasket is a material artifact that has component part some deformable material and bears some sealing function and has property some closed loop geometry.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1661"/>
  </rdf:Description>
