  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000250">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A diesel engine is an engine that ignites fuel through compression heat rather than spark ignition, requiring compression ignition and fuel injection systems.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um motor diesel é um motor que inflama combustível através do calor de compressão em vez de ignição por centelha, requerendo sistemas de ignição por compressão e injeção de combustível.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions for this constructive type. While compression ignition is characteristic of diesel engines, under OWA we cannot be certain that any engine with compression ignition systems is necessarily a diesel engine - there could be hybrid or specialized engines with similar mechanisms that should not be auto-classified as standard diesel engines without expert validation.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b971"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b968"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b969"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b967"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b970"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000264"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">DieselEngine(x) → Engine(x) ∧ ∃s(CompressionIgnitionSystem(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)) ∧ ∃f(FuelInjectionSystem(f) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,f)) ∧ ∃p(CompressionIgnitionProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DIESEL ENGINE&gt; is  an &lt;INTERNAL COMBUSTION ENGINE&gt; and a &lt;RECIPROCATING PISTON ENGINE&gt; in which ignition of the fuel injected into the cylinder is performed by the heat of compression of the air charge</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] An internal combustion engine in which ignition of the fuel injected into the cylinder is performed by the heat of compression of the air charge.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] An internal combustion engine in which ignition of the fuel injected into the cylinder is performed by the heat of compression of the air charge.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">A diesel engine is necessarily an engine that has compression ignition system and fuel injection system and participates in compression ignition process.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">motor diesel</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">diesel engine</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/DifferentialPressureMeasurementAndTransmissionProcess">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000036"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">differential pressure measurement and transmission process</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de medição e transmissão de pressão diferencial</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b790">
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b791"/>
    <rdf:first rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000084"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000074">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2915"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2913"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2916"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000092"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2914"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">shell and tube heat exchanger</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">trocador de calor de casco e tubos</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um trocador de calor de casco e tubos é um trocador de calor que possui um feixe de tubos contido espacialmente dentro de um casco envolvente.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A shell and tube heat exchanger is a heat exchanger that has a tube bundle spatially contained within a surrounding shell.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions for this constructive type to avoid false positives under OWA. Any equipment with a shell and tube bundle could theoretically be classified as a standard shell-and-tube heat exchanger, but specialized variants (like graphite shell-and-tube or custom multi-stream designs) should not be automatically forced into this maintenance category without domain expert validation.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every shell and tube heat exchanger is a heat exchanger that has a tube bundle as component part and has a shell as component part, where the tube bundle is spatially contained within the shell.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A tubular heat exchanger in which a tube bundle is surrounded by a shell.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SHELL AND TUBE HEAT EXCHANGER&gt; is a &lt;TUBULAR HEAT EXCHANGER&gt; in which a tube bundle is surrounded by a shell</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A tubular heat exchanger in which a tube bundle is surrounded by a shell.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">ShellAndTubeHeatExchanger(x) → HeatExchanger(x) ∧ ∃tb(TubeBundle(tb) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,tb)) ∧ ∃s(Shell(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s) ∧ spatiallyContains(s,tb))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
