  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000265">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma junta de expansão é um artefato material que possui a função projetada de acomodar expansão e contração térmica entre componentes conectados através de flexibilidade inerente, mantendo a integridade estrutural.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An expansion joint is a material artifact that bears the designed function of accommodating thermal expansion and contraction between connected components through inherent flexibility while maintaining structural integrity.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every expansion joint is a material artifact that bears a thermal expansion accommodation function and has a flexibility function, and every material artifact that bears a thermal expansion accommodation function and has a flexibility function is an expansion joint.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;EXPANSION JOINT&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;JOINT&gt; that makes allowance for thermal expansion of the parts joined without distortion</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] Flexible joint between two pipes to receive expansion from the pipes.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A device or completion component designed to enable relative movement between two fixed assemblies in the event of thermal expansion or contraction.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A device in a length of pipe that allows some pipe length expansion or contraction.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">junta de expansão</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">expansion joint</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (ExpansionJoint(x) ↔ (MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃f(ThermalExpansionAccommodationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃g(FlexibilityFunction(g) ∧ hasFunction(x,g))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1239"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/SecondaryWinding">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/TransformerWinding"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">secondary winding</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">enrolamento secundário</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000207">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every actuator is an assembly that has the function of converting external energy into controlled kinetic motion.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A transducer that is intended to convert energy (electric, mechanical, pneumatic or hydraulic) from an external source into kinetic energy (motion) in response to a signal or or power input.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object for changing a signal into a corresponding movement.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] An actuator is a type of motor for moving or controlling a mechanism or system. Actuator's are a vital part of offshore operations.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;ACTUATOR&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that is capable of &lt;ACTUATING&gt;</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An actuator is an assembly that bears an actuation function to convert energy from an external source into kinetic motion in response to control signals.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um atuador é um conjunto que possui uma função de atuação para converter energia de uma fonte externa em movimento cinético em resposta a sinais de controle.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">actuator</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">atuador</rdfs:label>
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000207"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b49"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Actuator(x) ↔ Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f (ActuationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000220">
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b338"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Burner(x) ↔ (Heater(x) ∧ ∃f (CombustionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">burner</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">queimador</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A burner is a heater that releases thermal energy by burning a combustible mixture of fuel and air.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um queimador é um aquecedor que libera energia térmica através da queima de uma mistura combustível de combustível e ar.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;BURNER&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that is intended to release thermal energy by burning a combustible mixture</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every burner is a heater that has the function of combustion, which is realized by burning a fuel-air mixture to release thermal energy.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FluidMixturePortion">
