  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000137">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">medidor de sequência de fases</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">phase sequence meter</rdfs:label>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2299"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A phase sequence meter is an electric measuring instrument that bears a phase sequence measurement function to determine and indicate the sequence in which the instantaneous voltages of phase conductors reach their maximum value in a polyphase electrical system.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um medidor de sequência de fases é um instrumento de medição elétrica que possui uma função de medição de sequência de fases para determinar e indicar a sequência na qual as tensões instantâneas dos condutores de fase atingem seu valor máximo em um sistema elétrico polifásico.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;PHASE SEQUENCE METER&gt; is an &lt;ELECTRIC VARIABLE MEASURING INSTRUMENT&gt; that indicates, on a polyphase system, the sequence in which the instantaneous voltage of the phase conductors reach their maximum value</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(PhaseSequenceMeter(x) ↔ ElectricMeasuringInstrument(x) ∧ ∃f(PhaseSequenceMeasurementFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃s(PolyphaseElectricalSignal(s) ∧ hasInput(x,s)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every phase sequence meter is an electric measuring instrument that has the function to measure phase sequence and has as input polyphase electrical signals.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1342">
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1336"/>
