  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000077">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">valve</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A valve is an assembly that bears a flow control function to permit, obstruct, regulate, or divert fluid streams.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula é um conjunto que possui uma função de controle de fluxo para permitir, obstruir, regular ou desviar correntes de fluido.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A fluid regulator that can be used to control (i.e. permit, obstruct, regulate or divert) a fluid stream.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] Any of several valves:  plug, gate, butterfly, needle, etc., used in oil field operations.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A fluid regulator that can be used to control (i.e. permit, obstruct, regulate or divert) a fluid stream.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;VALVE&gt; is a &lt;FLUID REGULATOR&gt; that can be used to control (i.e. permit, obstruct, regulate or divert) a fluid stream</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3318"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3317"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3316"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Might be too restrictive to define as sufficient being a material artifact and having a flow control function.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every valve is a material artifact that has the function to control fluid flow by permitting, obstructing, regulating, or diverting fluid streams.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Valve(x) ↔ MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃f(FlowControlFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3026">
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3027"/>
    <rdf:first rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b676">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ComparisonElement"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/StructuralSupportFunction">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3138"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3137"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/DesignedFunction"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in a StructuralSupportProcess and that consists in providing mechanical support, load distribution, or structural integrity within an engineered system through a flat, planar configuration.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de suporte estrutural</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">structural support function</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/TemperatureSignal">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">sinal de temperatura</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">temperature signal</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000362">
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Transducer(x) ↔ Instrument(x) ∧ ∃f (TransductionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;TRANSDUCER&gt; is an &lt;ENERGY CONVERTER&gt; that is capable of converting a &lt;PROCESS VARIABLE&gt; in one form or magnitude of energy to another form or magnitude of the same energy</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] An artefact that accepts information in the form of a physical or chemical variable (its input variable) and converts it into an output variable of the same or another nature, according to a definite law.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[isa5_1] a general term for a device, which can be a primary element, transmitter, relay, converter or other device, that receives information in the form of one or more physical quantities, modifies the information or its form, or both if required, and produces a resultant output signal.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A transducer is an instrument that bears a TransductionFunction to convert information from one form or magnitude of energy to another form or magnitude.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um transdutor é um instrumento que possui uma FunçãoDeTransdução para converter informação de uma forma ou magnitude de energia para outra forma ou magnitude.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every transducer is an instrument that has the designed function to convert energy or signal forms while preserving information content.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3165"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">transducer</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">transdutor</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ShaftSeal">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">vedação de eixo</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">shaft seal</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1789">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/HeatTransferProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/SeparateVapourSpace">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">espaço separado de vapor</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">separate vapour space</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000232">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">condensador</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">condenser</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every condenser is a heat exchanger that bears a condensation function, and every heat exchanger that bears a condensation function is a condenser.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b619"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A condenser is a heat exchanger that bears a designed function to condense vapor to liquid by removing latent heat of vaporization.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um condensador é um trocador de calor que possui uma função projetada para condensar vapor em líquido removendo o calor latente de vaporização.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A cooler that is intended to change a vapour to liquid.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CONDENSER&gt; is a &lt;COOLER&gt; that has a capability of  &lt;CONDENSING&gt; a &lt;FLUID&gt; from &lt;VAPOUR&gt; to &lt;LIQUID&gt;</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Condenser(x) ↔ (HeatExchanger(x) ∧ ∃f(CondensationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b435">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/SeparationProcess"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/StorageChamber">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">storage chamber</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">câmara de armazenamento</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/CombustionGasPortion">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">combustion gas portion</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">porção de combustão de gás</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000284">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um detector de gás é um detector que tem a função projetada de detectar a presença de uma concentração especificada de um gás.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A gas detector is a detector that has the designed function to sense the presence of a specified concentration of a gas.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">detector de gás</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">gas detector</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(GasDetector(x) ↔ (Detector(x) ∧ ∃f(GasDetectionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1619"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every gas detector is a detector that bears a GasDetectionFunction and has a GasDetectingMeasuringElement as component part at all times.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;GAS DETECTOR&gt; is a &lt;DETECTOR&gt; and a &lt;GAS DETECTING INSTRUMENT&gt; using a &lt;GAS DETECTING MEASURING ELEMENT&gt; that is intended to sense the presence of a specified concentration of a gas</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A detector that is intended to sense the presence of a specified concentration of a gas.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A detector that is intended to sense the presence of a specified concentration of a gas.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/LocalTemperatureDisplay">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">local temperature display</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">display local de temperatura</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PressureSignal">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pressure signal</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">sinal de pressão</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b811">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/AirIntake"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/Absorber">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">absorvedor</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">absorber</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Absorber(x) ↔ (Separator(x) ∧ ∃f(AbsorptionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b14"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An absorber is a pressure vessel that realizes an absorption function for selective mass transfer of components from a fluid mixture into an absorbent phase.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um absorvedor é um vaso de pressão que realiza uma função de absorção para transferência seletiva de massa de componentes de uma mistura fluida para uma fase absorvente.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A vertical, cylindrical vessel that recovers heavier (longer carbon chain) hydrocarbons from a mixture of lighter hydrocarbons.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;ABSORBER&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that has a capability of &lt;ABSORBING&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A functional object that absorbs.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every absorber is a separator that has the function to absorb specific components from fluid mixtures through mass transfer to an absorbent phase</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
