  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000298">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">atuador hidráulico</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">hydraulic actuator</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1869"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1870"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1871"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000207"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] An actuator intended to be operated by hydraulic power.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] An actuator intended to be operated by hydraulic power.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;HYDRAULIC ACTUATOR&gt; is an &lt;INSTRUMENTATION ITEM&gt; and a &lt;CONTROLLED ACTUATOR&gt; and a &lt;HYDRAULICALLY ACTUATED ARTEFACT&gt;</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um atuador hidráulico é um atuador que converte pressão de fluido hidráulico em movimento mecânico através de transmissão de potência hidráulica.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A hydraulic actuator is an actuator that converts hydraulic fluid pressure into mechanical motion through hydraulic power transmission.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every hydraulic actuator is an actuator that has hydraulic fluid portion as input and participates in hydraulic to mechanical energy conversion process.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive classification based on hydraulic power source. Under Open World Assumption, asserting equivalence could incorrectly classify complex hydraulic-mechanical hybrid systems or specialized equipment containing hydraulic actuator components as standard hydraulic actuators.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(HydraulicActuator(x) → Actuator(x) ∧ ∃y(HydraulicFluidPortion(y) ∧ hasInput(x,y)) ∧ ∃z(HydraulicToMechanicalEnergyConversionProcess(z) ∧ participatesIn(x,z)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b215">
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b216"/>
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b212"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000078">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3332"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">valve body</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">corpo de válvula</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;VALVE BODY&gt; is a &lt;VALVE COMPONENT&gt; and a &lt;CONTAINER&gt; that is the main fluid or pressure containing component of a valve, housing and supporting the working components</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type - the structural characteristics of being the main pressure-containing housing component are necessary conditions but may not be sufficient under OWA, as various specialized valve body configurations exist that might contain additional components or have hybrid designs that could lead to false positive classifications.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A ValveComponent that bears a ContainmentFunction and that serves as the main fluid and pressure containing component of a valve, housing and supporting the working components.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um ValveComponent que porta uma ContainmentFunction e que serve como o principal componente de contenção de fluido e pressão de uma válvula, alojando e suportando os componentes de trabalho.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every valve body is a valve component that contains and supports valve working components and bears the function of fluid and pressure containment.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(ValveBody(x) → ValveComponent(x) ∧ ∃f(ContainmentFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃y(WorkingComponent(y) ∧ houses(x,y)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2036">
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2030"/>
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2037"/>
  </rdf:Description>
