  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000251">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">elemento medidor de pressão diferencial</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">differential pressure measuring element</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um elemento de pressão que porta uma função de medição de pressão diferencial e que consiste em detectar a diferença de pressão entre duas mídias fluidas ou pontos de conexão para permitir a medição de pressão diferencial através de deflexão mecânica proporcional à diferença de pressão.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A pressure element that bears a differential pressure measurement function and that consists in sensing the pressure difference between two fluid media or connection points to enable measurement of differential pressure through mechanical deflection proportional to the pressure difference.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b989"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DIFFERENTIAL PRESSURE MEASURING ELEMENT&gt; is a &lt;PRESSURE MEASURING ELEMENT&gt; for the measurement of &lt;DIFFERENTIAL PRESSURE&gt;</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">DifferentialPressureMeasuringElement equivalentTo PressureElement and bearerOf some DifferentialPressureMeasurementFunction</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(DifferentialPressureMeasuringElement(x) ↔ (PressureElement(x) ∧ ∃f(DifferentialPressureMeasurementFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000274">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A system that burns waste in an elevated flame in the open air.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A burner on a remote line used for disposal of hydrocarbons during clean-up, emergency shut downs and for disposal of small volume waste streams of mixed gasses that cannot easily or safely be separated.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[DEXPI] An artefact and waste gas emitter that is intended to burn waste gas in secure distance from the plant or platform.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] The burning of unwanted gas through a pipe (also called a flare).</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FLARE&gt; is a &lt;BURNER&gt; that has a capability of &lt;FLARING&gt;</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flare</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">flare</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um flare é um queimador que descarta com segurança gases indesejados através de combustão controlada em local elevado.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A flare is a burner that safely disposes of unwanted gases through controlled combustion at an elevated location.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1393"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every flare is a burner that bears a waste gas disposal function and has component parts flare tip, flare stack, and pilot system.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Flare(x) ↔ (Burner(x) ∧ ∃f (WasteGasDisposalFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2929">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/NoiseSilencingProcess"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/RemovedMaterial">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">material de removido</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">removed material</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000330">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um transmissor de posição é um transmissor que mede posição ou deslocamento e o converte em um sinal de saída padronizado.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A position transmitter is a transmitter that measures position or displacement and converts it to a standardized output signal.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every position transmitter is a transmitter that has the function of position transmission and receives position or displacement signals as input.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2514"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">transmissor de posição</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">position transmitter</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(PositionTransmitter(x) ↔ Transmitter(x) ∧ ∃f(PositionTransmissionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃s(PositionSignal(s) ∧ hasInput(x,s)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[isa5_1] ISA 5.1 tag abbreviation 'ZT'. First letter 'Z': Position, Dimension. Succeeding letters: 'T' = Transmit.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;POSITION TRANSMITTER&gt;is a &lt;PROCESS VARIABLE TRANSMITTER&gt; and a &lt;POSITION MEASURING INSTRUMENT&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A transmitter that is producing a standardized output signal dependent of a received input signal from a position detector.</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/InjectionProcess">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de injeção</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">injection process</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/TemperatureSensingProcess">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de sensoriamento de temperatura</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">temperature sensing process</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b727">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FlowMeasurementProcess"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b295">
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b290"/>
    <rdf:rest rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#nil"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/GaseousFuelPortion">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">porção gasoso de combustível</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">gaseous fuel portion</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000247">
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b902"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">analisador de ponto de orvalho</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">dew point analyser</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um analisador de ponto de orvalho é um instrumento que possui uma função de medição de ponto de orvalho.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A dew point analyser is an instrument that bears a dew point measurement function.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DEW POINT ANALYSER&gt; is a &lt;PROCESS ANALYSER&gt; intended to determine the dew point of a substance</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] An analysing instrument intended to determine the dew point of a substance.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(DewPointAnalyser(x) ↔ Instrument(x) ∧ ∃f(DewPointMeasurementFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every dew point analyser is an instrument that has the function to determine the dew point of a substance</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2927">
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2925"/>
    <rdf:rest rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#nil"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000097">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A blow down valve is a valve that bears a designed function for rapid depressurization of high pressure systems.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula de blow down é uma válvula que possui uma função projetada para despressurização rápida de sistemas de alta pressão.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula de blow down</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">blow down valve</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (BlowDownValve(x) ↔ Valve(x) ∧ ∃f (RapidDepressurizationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A valve that can be used for rapid depressurizing of a high pressure system.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;BLOW DOWN VALVE is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;VALVE&gt; that can be used for rapid depressurizing of a high pressure system</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b263"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every blow down valve is a valve that has the function of rapid depressurization.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2949">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/SolidBulkStorageFunction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
