  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PressureField">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pressure field</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">campo de pressão</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000080">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2840"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A MaterialArtifact that has a sealing surface component and participates in valve closing processes, consisting in that part of a valve against which the closure element bears to provide tight shutoff.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um MaterialArtifact que possui um componente de superfície de vedação e participa em processos de fechamento de válvulas, consistindo na parte da válvula contra a qual o elemento de fechamento se apoia para proporcionar vedação hermética.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every Seat is a MaterialArtifact that has some sealing surface component at all times and participates in some valve closing process.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type based on physical configuration. Under OWA, sufficient conditions for 'seat' based solely on structural properties could lead to false positives where other valve components with sealing surfaces are incorrectly classified as seats.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">assento</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">seat</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] That part of a valve against which the closure element (gate, ball) affects a tight shutoff.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Seat(x) → MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃y(SealingSurface(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y)) ∧ ∃z(ValveClosingProcess(z) ∧ participatesIn(x,z)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/MeasurementElement">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">elemento de medição</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">measurement element</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2935">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/AcousticTreatmentElement"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000364">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A device attached to the topmost tubing joint in the wellhead to support the tubing string.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A slip set or donut that suspends and holds the top of the tubing in the wellhead.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;TUBING HANGER&gt; is a &lt;WELL STRING HANGER&gt; that is installed on top of the tubing string and supports the string when landed in the tubing hanger or tubing head.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A well string hanger that is used for production tubing. The tubing hanger incorporates a sealing system to ensure that the tubing conduit and annulus are hydraulically isolated.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(TubingHanger(x) ↔ (Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(TubingSupportFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃s(SealingSystem(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)) ∧ ∃m(SupportMechanism(m) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,m)) ∧ ∃c(TubingConnection(c) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,c))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3213"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A tubing hanger is an assembly that supports tubing strings in wellheads with integrated sealing to isolate tubing conduit from annulus.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um suporte de coluna de produção é um conjunto que suporta colunas de produção em cabeças de poço com vedação integrada para isolar o conduto da coluna do anular.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every tubing hanger is an assembly that bears a tubing support function and has component parts including a sealing system, support mechanism, and tubing connection.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">suporte de coluna de produção</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">tubing hanger</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2914">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/Shell"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000270">
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every fired heater is a heater that bears a FiredHeatingFunction</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FIRED HEATER&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;HEATER&gt; in which the heat converted from burning solids, liquids or gas is transferred to a media</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] Is a fired heat transfer equipment intended to burn fuel and to transfer the heat of combustion to a liquid without vaporising the liquid.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">fired heater</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">aquecedor a combustão</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(FiredHeater(x) ↔ (Heater(x) ∧ ∃f(FiredHeatingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um aquecedor a combustão é um aquecedor que queima combustível (sólido, líquido ou gasoso) para gerar calor para transferência para um fluido de processo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A fired heater is a heater that burns fuel (solid, liquid, or gas) to generate heat for transfer to a process fluid medium.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1334"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000159">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A vibration transmitter is a transmitter that measures mechanical vibrations and produces an output signal proportional to the measured vibration parameters.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um transmissor de vibração é um transmissor que mede vibrações mecânicas e produz um sinal de saída proporcional aos parâmetros de vibração medidos.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every vibration transmitter is a transmitter that has a vibration signal as input and bears a vibration measurement function.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">transmissor de vibração</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">vibration transmitter</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A transmitter of which the output is proportional to a measured vibration.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;VIBRATION TRANSMITTER&gt; is a &lt;PROCESS VARIABLE TRANSMITTER&gt; and a &lt;VIBRATION MEASURING INSTRUMENT&gt;</skos:definition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3383"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (VibrationTransmitter(x) ↔ (Transmitter(x) ∧ ∃v (VibrationSignal(v) ∧ hasInput(x,v)) ∧ ∃f (VibrationMeasurementFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b29">
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b25"/>
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b30"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/TemperatureElement">
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3072"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A detecting element intended to sense temperature.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A detecting element intended to sense temperature.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A temperature element is an instrument that bears a temperature sensing function.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um elemento de temperatura é um instrumento que possui uma função de sensoreamento de temperatura.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(TemperatureElement(x) ↔ DetectingElement(x) ∧ ∃f(TemperatureSensingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">temperature element</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">elemento de temperatura</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every temperature element is a detecting element that has the function to sense temperature</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
