  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000117">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A flow indicator is an indicator that is designed to indicate flow rates using a flow measuring element and display element.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um indicador de fluxo é um indicador projetado para indicar taxas de fluxo usando um elemento de medição de fluxo e elemento de exibição.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">indicador de fluxo</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flow indicator</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FLOW INDICATOR&gt; is an &lt;INSTRUMENTATION ITEM&gt; and a &lt;FLOW MEASURING INSTRUMENT&gt; and a &lt;INDICATOR&gt; that, using a &lt;FLOW MEASURING ELEMENT&gt;, is specially and exclusively designed for &lt;INDICATING&gt; a &lt;FLOW RATE&gt;</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every flow indicator is an instrument that bears a flow indication function and has a flow measuring element and display element as component parts.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1485"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (FlowIndicator(x) ↔ (Instrument(x) ∧ ∃f(FlowIndicationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃e(FlowMeasuringElement(e) ∧ hasComponentPartAtSomeTime(x,e)) ∧ ∃d(DisplayElement(d) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,d))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ElectricalTerminal">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">electrical terminal</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">terminal elétrico</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000108">
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (DiaphragmValve(x) → Valve(x) ∧ ∃d,p (ResilientDiaphragm(d) ∧ Port(p) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,d) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">diaphragm valve</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula de diafragma</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b943"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b945"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b944"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000077"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Since this is a constructive type defined by physical mechanism (diaphragm closure), necessary conditions are used to avoid over-classification under the Open World Assumption. Not every equipment with a diaphragm component should automatically be classified as a diaphragm valve - the structural differentia requires domain validation.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DIAPHRAGM VALVE&gt; is a &lt;MEMBRANE VALVE&gt; where the closure member is a resilient diaphragm being forced against a port</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A membrane valve that is a membrane valve where the closure member is a resilient diaphragm being forced against a port.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula de diafragma é uma válvula que usa um diafragma resiliente forçado contra uma porta como seu mecanismo de fechamento para controlar o fluxo de fluido.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A diaphragm valve is a valve that uses a resilient diaphragm forced against a port as its closure mechanism to control fluid flow.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every diaphragm valve is a valve that has a resilient diaphragm as component part and has a port as component part and participates in diaphragm closure processes.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000212">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] The positively charged site in a cell. Oxidation site. The site of metal loss in corrosion.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that is capable of emitting positive charge carriers to and/or receiving negative charge carriers from the medium of lower conductivity.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;ANODE&gt; is an &lt;ELECTRICAL DEVICE&gt; that has a capability of &lt;EMITTING&gt; positive charge carriers to, and/or &lt;RECEIVING&gt; negative charge carriers from, the medium of lower conductivity</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] The half of a battery that is positively charged and to which anions migrate by electrostatic attraction.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um ânodo é um equipamento elétrico que possui a função de servir como eletrodo positivo em processos eletroquímicos, capaz de emitir portadores de carga positiva para e/ou receber portadores de carga negativa de um meio de menor condutividade.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An anode is electrical equipment that bears the function of serving as the positive electrode in electrochemical processes, capable of emitting positive charge carriers to and/or receiving negative charge carriers from a medium of lower conductivity.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Anode(x) ↔ ElectricalEquipment(x) ∧ ∃f(AnodeFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">anode</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">ânodo</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every anode is electrical equipment that has the function of electrochemical oxidation and has electrical connection and active material as component parts at all times.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b120"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000340">
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every rotary actuator is an actuator that participates in rotary motion processes.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um atuador rotativo é um atuador que causa movimento rotativo convertendo sinais de controle em saída mecânica rotacional controlada.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A rotary actuator is an actuator that causes rotary motion by converting control signals into controlled rotational mechanical output.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (RotaryActuator(x) → Actuator(x) ∧ ∃p (RotaryMotionProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">rotary actuator</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">atuador rotativo</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2740"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000207"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type based on rotary motion mechanism. Under OWA, providing sufficient conditions could lead to over-classification where any equipment that happens to produce rotary motion (motors, turbines, etc.) might be incorrectly classified as rotary actuators. The rotary motion differentia is necessary but requires domain expert validation to confirm it is sufficient for the actuator equipment category.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;ROTARY ACTUATOR&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and an &lt;ACTUATOR&gt; causing a rotary motion</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
