  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000342">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um Assembly que participa em movimento rotacional e tem um eixo do rotor como componente essencial, projetado para transferir energia mecânica através de movimento rotacional dentro de um conjunto de máquina.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An Assembly that participates in rotational motion and has a rotor shaft as an essential component, designed to transfer mechanical energy through rotational motion within a machine assembly.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2756"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;ROTOR&gt; is a &lt;MACHINE COMPONENT&gt; that is the rotating portion of a machine</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] The rotating shaft in a PDM motor.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">As a constructive type defined by physical configuration (rotating portion with shaft), providing sufficient conditions under OWA could lead to overclassification. Complex assemblies containing rotating elements might be incorrectly classified as rotors rather than their proper categories (motors, compressors, etc.).</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Rotor(x) → Assembly(x) ∧ ∃p(RotationalMotionProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)) ∧ ∃s(RotorShaft(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">rotor</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">rotor</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every Rotor is an Assembly that participates in some RotationalMotionProcess and has some rotor shaft as component part at all times.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000093">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;ANGLE VALVE&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;VALVE&gt; that has valve ports which are not in-line</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A variation of the globe valve in which the end connections are at right angles to each other, rather than being in line.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b108"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000077"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b109"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula angular é uma válvula que tem portas da válvula que não estão alinhadas, mas dispostas em ângulo uma em relação à outra.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An angle valve is a valve that has valve ports which are not in-line but arranged at an angle to each other.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type defined by geometric configuration. Under OWA, sufficient conditions for non-inline port arrangement could lead to false positives where complex multi-port manifolds or specialized valves with angular components get incorrectly classified as standard angle valves.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every angle valve is a valve that has a non-inline port arrangement.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">angle valve</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula angular</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (AngleValve(x) → Valve(x) ∧ ∃p (hasPart(x,p) ∧ NonInlinePortArrangement(p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1611">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/TopOutlet"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b345">
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b346"/>
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b340"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000111">
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every double block and bleed valve is a valve that has a primary seat and has a secondary seat and has a bleed port.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DOUBLE BLOCK AND BLEED VALVE&gt; is a &lt;BLOCK AND BLEED VALVE&gt; and a &lt;DOUBLE BLOCK VALVE&gt; that is incorporating two seats, each of which provides a seal, and a means of venting the space between the seats. The seats may isolate with the pressure differential acting in the same or in opposite directions depending on the design</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A block and bleed valve that is incorporating two seats, each of which provides a seal, and a means of venting the space between the seats. The seats may isolate with the pressure differential acting in the same or in opposite directions depending on the design.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive basis - the structural differentia (dual seats plus bleed port) defines necessary conditions, but under OWA we cannot assert that ANY artifact with these structural components is definitively a double block and bleed valve, as specialized multi-way valves or custom manifolds might contain similar mechanisms without being standard maintenance categories.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A double block and bleed valve is a valve that incorporates two seats each providing sealing capability and includes a means of venting the space between the seats.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula de bloqueio duplo e sangria é uma válvula que incorpora duas sedes, cada uma proporcionando capacidade de vedação, e inclui um meio de ventilação do espaço entre as sedes.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1082"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b1083"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000077"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula de bloqueio duplo e sangria</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">double block and bleed valve</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (DoubleBlockAndBleedValve(x) → (Valve(x) ∧ ∃p,s,b (PrimarySeat(p) ∧ SecondarySeat(s) ∧ BleedPort(b) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,p) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,b))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
