  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000347">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">agitador</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">shaker</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SHAKER&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that has the capability of &lt;SHAKING&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A piece of drilling equipment, usually with a vibrating screen, where drill cuttings are removed from the flowing mud.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] Abbreviation for shale shaker, the primary and probably most important device on the rig for removing drilled solids from the mud.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um agitador é um conjunto que possui uma função de agitação, capaz de produzir movimento vibratório ou oscilatório para processamento, agitação ou separação de materiais.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A shaker is an assembly that bears a shaking function, capable of producing vibrating or oscillating motion for material processing, agitation, or separation.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2879"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">Shaker(x) ↔ Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(ShakingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every shaker is an assembly that has the capability of shaking and contains a vibration mechanism and a shaking element.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b540">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ElectricalCurrentInterruptionProcess"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000363">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b3208"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(TransmitterHousing(x) → Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(EnclosureFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃c(TransmitterElectronicCircuit(c) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,c)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type based on physical structure as housing. Under OWA, sufficient conditions for transmitter housing would require specifying exact structural features (materials, dimensions, sealing mechanisms) that distinguish it from other instrument housings. The necessary conditions establish the core identity without risking false positives from other housing types that might share some structural features.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">invólucro de transmissor</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">transmitter housing</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um invólucro de transmissor é uma Assembly que possui uma EnclosureFunction e que tem um circuito eletrônico de transmissor como parte componente em todos os momentos, projetado para fornecer proteção ambiental e contenção física para componentes do transmissor.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A transmitter housing is an Assembly that bears an EnclosureFunction and that has a transmitter electronic circuit as a component part at all times, designed to provide environmental protection and physical containment for transmitter components.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;TRANSMITTER HOUSING&gt; is an &lt;INSTRUMENT HOUSING&gt; of a transmitter.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">TransmitterHousing ⊑ Assembly ⊓ ∃bearerOf.EnclosureFunction ⊓ ∃hasComponentPartAtAllTimes.TransmitterElectronicCircuit</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="na2a46d8928414473b41f08b70337d4d1b2522">
